          and unfaithfulness on the part of the bride during the engagement would
          have been punishable by death.    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Gabriel appeared to her and said, \u201CRejoice, beloved young woman,
        for the Lord is with you [[COMMENT(0)]] and you are anointed with great favor.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 1:28
        content: "  For Gabriel to say, \u201Cthe Lord is with you,\u201D could mean
          that Jesus, our Master, had been conceived in her womb. This was what bewildered
          Mary.    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Mary was deeply troubled over the words of the angel and bewildered
        over what this may mean for her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But the angel reassured her, saying, \u201CDo not yield to your fear,
        Mary, for the Lord has found delight in you and has chosen to surprise you
        with a wonderful gift. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'You will become pregnant with a baby boy, and you are to name him
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He will be supreme [[COMMENT(0)]] and will be known as the Son of
        the Highest. And the Lord God will enthrone him as King on the throne of
        his ancestor David. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:32
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "He will reign as King of Israel [[COMMENT(0)]] forever, and his reign
        will have no limit.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 1:33
        content: "  Or \u201CHouse of Jacob.\u201D    "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Mary said, \u201CBut how could this happen? I am still a virgin!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Gabriel answered, \u201CThe Spirit of Holiness will fall upon you
        and almighty God will spread his shadow of power over you in a cloud of glory!
        [[COMMENT(0)]] This is why the child born to you will be holy,  and he will
        be called the Son of God. "
      comments:
      - number: 1:35
        content: "  The Greek word used as a metaphor, \u201Cspread his shadow over
          you,\u201D is also the word used at Jesus\u2019 transfiguration when the
          cloud of glory overshadowed Jesus on the mountain ().      Jesus Christ
          is holy, born without sin in his bloodline, for his Father was God Almighty.
          He would become the only perfect sacrifice to take away our sin and remove
          its power and penalty from us.    "
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "What\u2019s more, your aged aunt, [[COMMENT(0)]] Elizabeth, has also
        become pregnant with a son. The \u2018barren one\u2019 is now in her sixth
        month. "
      comments:
      - number: 1:36
        content: "  The Greek word is \u201Crelative.\u201D Many scholars believe
          Elizabeth was Mary\u2019s maternal aunt.    "
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Not one promise from God is empty of power. Nothing is impossible
        with God!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 1:37
        content: "  This verse can be translated in two different ways: \u201CThere
          is nothing impossible with God\u201D or \u201CThe word of God will never
          fail.\u201D This translation has chosen to include both for this verse.    "
    - name: "38: Elizabeth\u2019s Prophecy to Mary"
      title: "Elizabeth\u2019s Prophecy to Mary"
      number: 38
      content: "Then Mary responded, saying, \u201CYes! I will be a mother for the
        Lord! [[COMMENT(0)]] As his servant, I accept whatever he has for me. May
        everything you have told me come to pass.\u201D And the angel left her."
      comments:
      - number: 1:38
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Afterward, Mary arose and hurried off to the hill country of Judea,
        to the village where Zechariah and Elizabeth lived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Arriving at their home, Mary entered the house and greeted Elizabeth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "At the moment her aunt heard Mary\u2019s voice, the baby [[COMMENT(0)]]
        within Elizabeth\u2019s womb jumped and kicked. And suddenly, Elizabeth was
        filled to overflowing with the Holy Spirit! "
      comments:
      - number: 1:41
        content: "  The Bible calls Elizabeth\u2019s yet-to-be-born son, John, a
          \u201Cbaby.\u201D    "
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "With a loud voice she prophesied with power:\u201CMary! You are a
        woman given the highest favorand privilege above all others,for your child
        [[COMMENT(0)]] is destined to bring God great delight."
      comments:
      - number: 1:42
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe fruit of your womb.\u201D This is the same word
          used for the \u201Cfruit\u201D of the tree of life in  . Jesus is \u201Cfruit\u201D
          for us to take in as our life supply.    "
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: How did I deserve such a remarkable honorto have the mother of my
        Lord [[COMMENT(0)]] come and visit me?
      comments:
      - number: 1:43
        content: '  An obvious prophetic revelation was given to Elizabeth from the
          Holy Spirit about what had happened with Mary.    '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: The moment you came in the door and greeted me,my baby danced inside
        me with joy!
      comments: []
    - name: "45: Mary\u2019s Prophetic Song"
      title: "Mary\u2019s Prophetic Song"
      number: 45
      content: "Great favor rests upon you, for you have believedevery word spoken
        to you from the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And Mary sang this song:\u201CMy soul is ecstatic, overflowing with
        praises to God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: My spirit bursts with joy over my life-giving God! [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 1:47
        content: "  Or \u201CSavior.\u201D The first recorded person to call Jesus
          Savior was his mother, Mary. She rejoices in God not simply as her Creator,
          but as Life Giver and Savior.    "
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: For he set his tender gaze upon me, his lowly servant girl. [[COMMENT(0)]]And
        from here on, everyone will knowthat I have been favored and blessed.
      comments:
      - number: 1:48
        content: "  The Aramaic text is \u201CHe set his gaze upon the willingness
          of his mother.\u201D    "
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: The Mighty One has worked a mighty miracle for me;holy is his name!
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: Mercy kisses all who fear him,from one generation to the next. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 1:50
        content: '  Mary is quoting    and  .    '
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: Mighty power flows from himto scatter all those who walk in pride.
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: Powerful princes he tears from their thronesand he lifts up the lowly
        to take their place.
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: Those who hunger for him will always be filled, [[COMMENT(0)]]but
        the smug and self-satisfied he will send away empty.
      comments:
      - number: 1:53
        content: '  Mary is quoting  .    '
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: Because he can never forget to show mercy,he has helped his chosen
        servant, Israel,
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "keeping his promises to Abraham [[COMMENT(0)]]and to his descendants
        forever.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 1:55
        content: '  Mary understood by revelation that the Christ child would fulfill
          the promises of mercy that God gave to Abraham. See  .    '
    - name: '56: The Birth of the Prophet John'
      title: The Birth of the Prophet John
      number: 56
      content: Before going home, Mary stayed with Elizabeth for about three months.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 1:56
        content: '  The cultural practice of the Hebrews was for the mother to do
          nothing but rest during the first three months of pregnancy.    '
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "When Elizabeth\u2019s pregnancy was full term, she gave birth to
        a son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: All her family, friends, and neighbors heard about it, and they too
        were overjoyed, for they realized that the Lord had showered his wonderful
        mercy upon her.
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'When the baby was eight days old, according to their custom, all
        the family and friends came together for the circumcision ceremony. [[COMMENT(0)]]
        Everyone assumed that the parents would name the baby Zechariah, after his
        father, '
      comments:
      - number: 1:59
        content: '  This ceremony was an important time of celebration in Jewish
          culture, for another child was born under the covenant of God with Israel.
          See  ;  .    '
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "but Elizabeth spoke up and said, \u201CNo, his name is John!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "\u201CWhat?\u201D they exclaimed. \u201CNo one in your family line
        has that name!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "So they gestured to the baby\u2019s father to ask what to name the
        child. "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: "He motioned for a writing tablet, and to the amazement of all, he
        wrote, \u201CHis name is John.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 1:63
        content: "  The name John means \u201CGod\u2019s gift\u201D or \u201CGod
          is gracious.\u201D    "
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: Instantly Zechariah could speak again. And his first words were praises
        to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'The fear of God fell on the people of their village, and the news
        of this astounding event traveled throughout the hill country of Judea. Everyone
        was in awe over it! '
      comments: []
    - name: "66: Zechariah\u2019s Prophecy"
      title: "Zechariah\u2019s Prophecy"
      number: 66
      content: "All who heard this news were astonished and wondered, \u201CSince
        a miracle brought his birth, what on earth will this child become? Clearly,
        God\u2019s presence is upon this child in a powerful way!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'Then Zechariah was filled to overflowing with the Holy Spirit and
        he prophesied, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "\u201CPraise be to the exalted Lord God of Israel,for he has seen
        us through eyes of grace,and he comes as our Hero-God to set us free!"
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: He appears to us as a mighty Savior,a trumpet of redemption [[COMMENT(0)]]
        from the house of David, his servant,
      comments:
      - number: 1:69
        content: "  Literal translation of the Aramaic. The Hebrew is \u201Ca horn
          of salvation,\u201D which signifies strength and fighting power.    "
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: just as he promised long agoby the words of his holy prophets.
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: They prophesied he would come one day and save usfrom every one of
        our enemiesand from the power of those who hate us. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 1:71
        content: '  Zechariah is quoting from  .    '
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: Now he has shown us the mercy promised to our ancestors,for he has
        remembered his holy covenant. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 1:72
        content: "  There is amazing Hebrew poetry contained in this passage. The
          names of John, Zechariah, and Elizabeth are all found in this verse. \u201CHe
          has shown us mercy\u201D or \u201CGod\u2019s gracious gift\u201D is found
          in the name John. \u201CHe has remembered\u201D is the name Zechariah.
          \u201CHis holy covenant\u201D is the name Elizabeth.    "
    - name: '73-75: '
      title: 
      number: 73-75
      content: He has rescued us from the power of our enemies,fulfilling the sacred
        oath he made with our father Abraham.Now we can boldly worship [[COMMENT(0)]]
        God with holy lives,living in purity as priests  in his presence every day!
      comments:
      - number: "1:73\u201375"
        content: "  Or \u201Cserve.\u201D      The word translated as \u201Cpurity\u201D
          here is a Hebraic homonym for \u201Cpriesthood.\u201D    "
