    - name: '76: '
      title: 
      number: 76
      content: 'And to you I prophesy, my little son,you will be known as the prophet
        of the Most High.You will be a forerunner,going before the face of Lord <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]to prepare hearts to embrace his ways. '
      comments:
      - number: 1:76
        content: '  Literal translation of the Aramaic.      Zechariah quotes from 
          .    '
    - name: '77: '
      title: 
      number: 77
      content: You will preach to his people the revelation of salvation,the cancellation
        of all our sins, to bring us back to God.
      comments: []
    - name: '78: '
      title: 
      number: 78
      content: "The splendor-light of heaven\u2019s glorious sunrise [[COMMENT(0)]]is
        about to break upon us in holy visitation,all because the merciful heart
        of our God is so very tender."
      comments:
      - number: 1:78
        content: "  Some believe this is a quote from  . Jesus the Savior is the
          dawning light of a new day to this dark world. This \u201Csunrise\u201D
          is the appearing of Jesus, our Dayspring.    "
    - name: '79: '
      title: 
      number: 79
      content: "The word from heaven will come to us [[COMMENT(0)]]with dazzling
        light to shine upon thosewho live in darkness, near death\u2019s dark shadow.
        And he will illuminate the path that leads to the way of peace.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 1:79
        content: "  Or \u201Cmanifestation from heaven\u201D as translated from the
          Aramaic.      Zechariah is quoting from    and  .    "
    - name: '80: '
      title: 
      number: 80
      content: Afterward, their son grew up and was strengthened by the Holy Spirit
        [[COMMENT(0)]] and he grew in his love for God. John chose to live in the
        lonely wilderness until the day of his public appearance to Israel.
      comments:
      - number: 1:80
        content: "  Both of John\u2019s parents were full of the Holy Spirit (vv. 
          ,  ). John was raised in a Spirit-filled home.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: The Birth of Jesus'
      title: The Birth of Jesus
      number: 1-2
      content: 'During those days, the Roman emperor, Caesar Augustus, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        ordered that the first census be taken throughout his empire. (Quirinius
        was the governor of Syria at that time.) '
      comments:
      - number: "2:1\u20132"
        content: "  It is ironic that the Roman emperors viewed themselves as \u201Cgods\u201D
          while the little baby born in a feeding trough was the true God incarnate.    "
    - name: '1-2: The Birth of Jesus'
      title: The Birth of Jesus
      number: 1-2
      content: 'During those days, the Roman emperor, Caesar Augustus, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        ordered that the first census be taken throughout his empire. (Quirinius
        was the governor of Syria at that time.) '
      comments:
