          The Aramaic word translated \u201Clife\u201D often refers to salvation.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "John kept preaching to the many crowds who came out to be baptized,
        \u201CYou are nothing but the offspring of venomous snakes, full of deception!
        Who warned you to repent before the coming wrath of God? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then turn away from your sins, turn to God, and let your changed
        life be proof. Don\u2019t think for a moment that it\u2019s enough to simply
        be the favored descendants of Abraham. That\u2019s not enough to save you.
        [[COMMENT(0)]] I\u2019m telling you, God could make more sons of Abraham
        out of stones if he chose to!"
      comments:
      - number: 3:8
        content: "  God values reformation over ritual. John\u2019s ministry was
          to prepare people for the appearing of Jesus Christ through repentance
          and baptism. Repentance breaks open the heart and changes our attitudes
          toward God. Baptism was a burial of those who repented, preparing them
          for the germination of Christ coming to live within by the new birth.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CEven now God\u2019s axe of judgment is poised to chop down
        your barren tree right down to its roots! And every tree that does not produce
        good fruit will be leveled and thrown into the fire.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The crowd kept asking him, \u201CWhat then are we supposed to do?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "John told them, \u201CGive food to the hungry, clothe the poor, and
        bless the needy.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 3:11
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201CThe one with two tunics is
          to share with him who has none, and he who has food is to do likewise.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Even the despised tax collectors came to John to be baptized, and
        they asked him, \u201CWhat are we to do to prove our hearts have changed?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBe honest,\u201D he replied. \u201CDon\u2019t demand more taxes
        than what the law requires.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 3:13
        content: '  True repentance is tied to actions, a change of heart and deeds,
          not just words.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAnd us?\u201D asked some soldiers. [[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CWhat
        about us?\u201DJohn answered them, \u201CBe content with what you earn. Never
        extort money or terrify others by threats of violence or be guilty of accusing
        the innocent.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 3:14
        content: '  The soldiers were likely temple police.    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: During those days, everyone was gripped with messianic expectations,
        believing the Messiah could come at any moment, and many began to wonder
        if John might be the Christ.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But John made it clear by telling them, \u201CThere is one coming
        who is mightier than I. He is supreme. [[COMMENT(0)]] In fact, I\u2019m not
        worthy of even being his slave.  I can only baptize you in this river, but
        he will baptize you into the Spirit of holiness and into his raging fire.   "
      comments:
      - number: 3:16
        content: "  The word translated \u201Csupreme\u201D is found only in the
          Aramaic text. John was a true prophet who pointed others to the Supreme
          One.      Or \u201Cloose his sandal strap,\u201D which only a slave would
          do.      The Aramaic text reads \u201CHe will baptize you into the Spirit
          of the Holy One and in light.\u201D A baptism of light or fire would cleanse
          and change a life, giving new power to live for God and deal with every
          issue that hinders love and passion from burning in our hearts. It is the
          baptism of the Holy Spirit that all believers need today.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He has in his hands a winnowing fork to clean up his threshing floor!
        [[COMMENT(0)]] He will separate the wheat from the chaff. The wheat he will
        gather into his barn, but he will burn the chaff in a fire that no one can
        ever put out!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 3:17
        content: "  The text is literally \u201Cin his hand is a winnowing fork.\u201D
          This was a small pitchfork used to separate the chaff from the grain.    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'John used many similar warnings as he preached the good news and
        prepared [[COMMENT(0)]] the people. '
      comments:
      - number: 3:18
        content: '  Translated from the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He even publicly rebuked Antipas, son of Herod, the governor of Galilee,
        for the many wicked things he had done. He fearlessly reprimanded him for
        seducing and marrying his sister-in-law, Herodias.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Baptism of Jesus'
      title: The Baptism of Jesus
      number: 20
      content: Adding to his many other sins, Herod had John seized and locked up
        in prison.
      comments: []
    - name: '21-22: The Ancestry of Jesus Christ'
      title: The Ancestry of Jesus Christ
      number: 21-22
      content: "One day, Jesus came to be baptized [[COMMENT(0)]] along with all
        the others. As he was consumed with the spirit of prayer,  the heavenly realm
        ripped open above him and the Holy Spirit descended from heaven in the form
        of a dove  and landed on him. Then God\u2019s audible voice was heard, saying,
        \u201CMy Son, you are my beloved one.  Through you I am fulfilled.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: "3:21\u201322"
        content: "  Jesus identified with sinners, even at his baptism. Although
          he had no sin, he chose to become one with sinners and was washed by John
          as a preview of what would happen when he became sin () and was judged
          for our sins at the cross.      We read about Jesus praying eight times
          in Luke\u2019s Gospel. (1) At his baptism Jesus prayed and the heavens
          were opened, revealing his sonship. Jesus asked the Father to send the
          Holy Spirit to strengthen him for his wilderness temptations (). (2) Jesus
          prayed in solitude, and miracles broke loose in his ministry (). (3) Jesus
          prayed all night before he chose his twelve companions (). (4) Jesus prayed
          for his apostles to receive the full revelation of who he is (). (5) When
          Jesus was about to be glorified in splendor on the mountain, he prayed,
          and his face glowed with a flashing light (). (6) Jesus prayed that he
