        God!\u201DJesus commanded the demons to come out of him, and they shouted,
        \u201CWe beg you, don\u2019t torture us!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Jesus asked the man, <JESUS>\u201CWhat is your name?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CMob,\u201D
        the demons answered. \u201CWe are a mob, [[COMMENT(0)]] for there are many
        of us here in this man. "
      comments:
      - number: 8:30
        content: "  The Greek word used for \u201Cmob\u201D is literally \u201Clegion,\u201D
          which was the largest unit of the Roman military and represented up to
          6,800 soldiers.    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "We beg you, don\u2019t banish us into the Abyss!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:31
        content: '  See  ;  . The Abyss is the place of imprisonment for Satan and
          his demons.    '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "On the hillside nearby, there was a large herd of pigs, and the demons
        pleaded with Jesus, \u201CLet us enter into the pigs.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So Jesus ordered all the \u201Cmob\u201D of demons to come out of
        the man and enter the pigs. The crazed herd of swine stampeded over the cliff
        into the lake and all of them drowned."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When the herders tending the pigs saw what had happened, they ran
        off in fear and reported it to the nearby town and throughout the countryside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then the people of the region came out to see for themselves what
        had happened. When they came to where Jesus was, they discovered the notorious
        madman totally set free. He was clothed, speaking intelligently, and sitting
        at the feet of Jesus. They were shocked! '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then eyewitnesses to the miracle reported all that they had seen
        and how Jesus completely delivered the demonized man from his torment.After
        hearing about such amazing power, the townspeople became frightened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Soon all the people of the region of the Gerasenes and the surrounding
        country pleaded with Jesus to leave them, for they were gripped with fear.
        So Jesus got into the boat, intending to return to Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But the man who had been set free begged Jesus over and over not
        to leave, saying, \u201CLet me be with you!\u201DJesus sent him away with
        these instructions: "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: More Miracles of Healing'
      title: More Miracles of Healing
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CReturn to your home and your family, and tell them all
        the wonderful things God has done for you.\u201D</JESUS> So the man went
        back and preached to everyone who would listen about the amazing miracle
        Jesus had worked in his life."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'When Jesus returned to Galilee, the crowds were overjoyed, for they
        had been waiting for him to arrive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41-42: '
      title: 
      number: 41-42
      content: "Just then, a man named Jairus, the leader of the local Jewish congregation,
        fell before Jesus\u2019 feet. He desperately begged him to come and heal
        his twelve-year-old daughter, his only child, because she was at the point
        of death.As Jesus started to go with him to his home to see her, a large
        crowd surrounded him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41-42: '
      title: 
      number: 41-42
      content: "Just then, a man named Jairus, the leader of the local Jewish congregation,
        fell before Jesus\u2019 feet. He desperately begged him to come and heal
        his twelve-year-old daughter, his only child, because she was at the point
        of death.As Jesus started to go with him to his home to see her, a large
        crowd surrounded him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'In the crowd that day was a woman who had suffered greatly for twelve
        years [[COMMENT(0)]] from slow bleeding. Even though she had spent all that
        she had on healers,  she was still suffering. '
      comments:
      - number: 8:43
        content: "  The daughter of Jairus was twelve years old; this woman had suffered
          for twelve years. Jesus touched the girl; the woman touched Jesus.     
          Translated from the Aramaic text, which states literally \u201Cthe house
          of healers.\u201D This phrase is not found in many Greek texts.    "
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: Pressing in through the crowd, she came up behind Jesus and touched
        the fringe [[COMMENT(0)]] of his garment. Instantly her bleeding stopped
        and she was healed.
      comments:
      - number: 8:44
        content: '  This was on the corner of the prayer shawl, and the tassel was
          meant to symbolize all of the commandments and promises of God. The woman
          was laying hold of a promise for healing.    '
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Jesus suddenly stopped and said to his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CSomeone
        touched me. Who was it?\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]While they all denied
        it, Peter pointed out, \u201CMaster, everyone is touching you, trying to
        get close to you. The crowds are so thick  we can\u2019t walk through all
        these people without being jostled.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 8:45
        content: "  Jesus already knew the answer to his question. He wanted the
          woman to come forward and acknowledge her healing.      There were many
          crowds around Jesus, the living Word. Many today crowd around the Bible,
          the written Word. But only those who \u201Ctouch\u201D the Scriptures in
          faith receive its promises, just like the sick woman received her healing.    "
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYes, but I felt power surge through me.
        Someone touched me to be healed, and they received their healing.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "When the woman realized she couldn\u2019t hide any longer, she came
        and fell trembling at Jesus\u2019 feet. Before the entire crowd she declared,
        \u201CI was desperate to touch you, Jesus, for I knew if I could just touch
        even the fringe of your garment [[COMMENT(0)]] I would be healed.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 8:47
        content: '  She was touching the hem of the robe of our anointed High Priest,
          Jesus. See  .    '
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CBeloved daughter, your faith in me
        released your healing. You may go with my peace.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "While Jesus was still speaking to the woman, someone came from Jairus\u2019
        house and told him, \u201CThere\u2019s no need to bother the Master any further.
        Your daughter has passed away. She\u2019s gone.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "When Jesus heard this, he turned to Jairus and said, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t
        yield to your fear. Have faith in me and she will live again.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "When they arrived at the house, Jesus allowed only Peter, John, and
        Jacob\u2014along with the child\u2019s parents\u2014to go inside. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Jesus told those left outside, who were sobbing and wailing with
        grief, <JESUS>\u201CStop crying. She is not dead; she\u2019s just asleep
        and must be awakened.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: They laughed at him, [[COMMENT(0)]] knowing for certain that she had
        died.
      comments:
      - number: 8:53
        content: "  They did not realize that Jesus was using \u201Csleep\u201D as
          a metaphor for death.    "
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Jesus approached the body, took the girl by her hand, and called
        out with a loud voice, <JESUS>\u201CMy sleeping child, awake! Rise up!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '55-56: '
      title: 
      number: 55-56
      content: Instantly her spirit returned to her body and she stood up. [[COMMENT(0)]]Jesus
        directed her stunned parents to give her something to eat and ordered them
        to tell no one what just happened.
      comments:
      - number: "8:55\u201356"
        content: '  This chapter contains four great miracles of Jesus Christ: (1)
          over nature, for he stilled the wind and waves; (2) over demons, for he
          cast out a mob of evil spirits; (3) over disease, for he healed the hemorrhaging
          woman; and (4) over death, for he restored the life of this twelve-year-old
          girl.  '
    - name: '55-56: '
      title: 
      number: 55-56
      content: Instantly her spirit returned to her body and she stood up. [[COMMENT(0)]]Jesus
        directed her stunned parents to give her something to eat and ordered them
        to tell no one what just happened.
      comments:
      - number: "8:55\u201356"
        content: '  This chapter contains four great miracles of Jesus Christ: (1)
          over nature, for he stilled the wind and waves; (2) over demons, for he
          cast out a mob of evil spirits; (3) over disease, for he healed the hemorrhaging
          woman; and (4) over death, for he restored the life of this twelve-year-old
          girl.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Sends Out His Apostles'
      title: Jesus Sends Out His Apostles
      number: 1
      content: 'Jesus summoned together his twelve apostles [[COMMENT(0)]] and imparted
        to them authority over every demon and the power to heal every disease. '
      comments:
      - number: 9:1
        content: '  As translated from certain Greek manuscripts and implied in the
          context.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he commissioned them to proclaim God\u2019s kingdom and to heal
        the sick to demonstrate that the kingdom had arrived. As he sent them out,
        he gave them these instructions: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CTake nothing extra on your journey.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>Just go as you are. Don\u2019t carry a staff, a backpack, food, money,
        not even a change of clothes.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 9:3
        content: '  Why did Jesus tell them to go empty-handed? To trust and walk
          in faith. But also because they already had the five items they were told
          not to bring, as their spiritual counterparts are found in him (i.e., he
          is our treasure, our strength, our living bread, our provider, and our
          righteousness).    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>Whatever home welcomes you as a guest, remain there and make
        it your base of ministry.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>And wherever your ministry is rejected, you are to leave that
        town and shake the dust off your shoes as a testimony before them.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:5
        content: "  Shaking the dust off their feet would be a statement against
          the people who had rejected the gospel, that the messengers would not be
          responsible for their fate. More than a metaphor, this was an actual custom
          of the day. However, the words \u201Cbefore them\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Cagainst them.\u201D Shaking the dust off their feet did not mean
          they were to stomp off offended and angry, but that they would move on
          with no defilement or unforgiveness in their hearts toward those who rejected
          their message. If they did not do that, they would take the \u201Cdust\u201D
          of that offense to the next place they ministered.    "
    - name: '6: Herod Perplexed'
      title: Herod Perplexed
      number: 6
      content: "The apostles departed and went into the villages with the wonderful
        news of God\u2019s kingdom, and they healed diseases wherever they went."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now, Herod, the governor, was confused and perplexed when he heard
        reports of all the miracles of Jesus and his apostles. Many were saying,
        \u201CJohn the Baptizer has come back to life!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Others said, \u201CThis has to be Elijah who has reappeared or one
        of the prophets of old who has risen from the dead.\u201D These were the
        rumors circulating throughout the land.Herod exclaimed, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Jesus Feeds Thousands'
      title: Jesus Feeds Thousands
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWho is this Man? I keep hearing about him over and over. It
        can\u2019t be the prophet John; I had him beheaded!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]
        So, Herod was very eager to meet Jesus."
      comments:
      - number: 9:9
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Months later, [[COMMENT(0)]] the apostles returned from their ministry
        tour and told Jesus all the wonders and miracles they had witnessed. Jesus,
        wanting to be alone with the Twelve, quietly slipped away with them toward
        Bethsaida.   '
      comments:
      - number: 9:10
        content: "  Matthew infers that they had been sent north and east, possibly
          as far as Persia to preach to the Jewish residents there, which would take
          them months to return.      Bethsaida means \u201Chouse of fishing.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Crowds soon found out about it and took off after him. When they
        caught up with Jesus, he graciously welcomed them all, taught them more about
        God\u2019s kingdom, and healed all who were sick."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "As the day wore on, the Twelve came to Jesus and told him, \u201CIt\u2019s
        getting late. You should send the crowds to the surrounding villages and
        farms to get something to eat and find shelter for the night. There\u2019s
        nothing to eat here in the middle of nowhere.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CYou have the food to feed them.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]They replied, \u201CAll we have are these five small loaves
        of bread and two dried fish. Do you really expect us to go buy food for all
        these people? "
      comments:
      - number: 9:13
        content: "  In the Greek text, the word    here is emphatic. Jesus told his
          disciples they had food to give to others. Because Jesus lives within us,
          we can give others the living bread and, if need be, multiply food for
          others to eat. We are to focus on what we have, not on what we don\u2019t
          have.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "There are nearly five thousand men here, with women and children
        besides!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]He told his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CHave them
        all sit down in groups of fifty each.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 9:14
        content: '  There were likely ten thousand people whom Jesus miraculously
          fed that day.      There is an interesting correlation between seating
          the people in groups of fifty and the feast of Pentecost. Fifty was the
          number of days between Passover and Pentecost.    '
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: 'After everyone was seated, Jesus took the five loaves and two fish,
        and gazing into the heavenly realm he gave thanks for the food. Then, in
        the presence of his disciples, he broke off pieces of bread and fish, and
        kept giving more to each disciple to give to the crowd. It was multiplying
        before their eyes!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: 'After everyone was seated, Jesus took the five loaves and two fish,
        and gazing into the heavenly realm he gave thanks for the food. Then, in
        the presence of his disciples, he broke off pieces of bread and fish, and
        kept giving more to each disciple to give to the crowd. It was multiplying
        before their eyes!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jesus Prophesies His Death and Resurrection'
      title: Jesus Prophesies His Death and Resurrection
      number: 17
      content: "So everyone ate until they were filled, and afterward the disciples
        gathered up the leftovers\u2014it came to exactly twelve baskets full!"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "One time, Jesus was praying in a quiet place with his disciples nearby.
        He went to them and asked, <JESUS>\u201CWho do people think I am?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They answered, \u201CSome are convinced you\u2019re the prophet John
        who has returned. Others say you are Elijah, or perhaps one of the Jewish
        prophets brought back from the dead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jesus asked them, <JESUS>\u201CBut who do you believe that I am?\u201D</JESUS>Peter
        said, \u201CYou are the Anointed One, God\u2019s Messiah!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Jesus gave them strict orders not to tell this to anyone yet, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: What it Means to Follow Jesus'
      title: What it Means to Follow Jesus
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe Son of Man</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>is destined
        to experience great suffering and face complete rejection by the Jewish leaders
        and religious hierarchy.</JESUS>    <JESUS>He will be killed and raised back
        to life on the third day.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 9:22
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe true Man.\u201D      The Greek text is literally
          \u201Cthe elders, chief priests, and scribes.\u201D These three groups
          were represented in the religious hierarchy of the Sanhedrin, a council
          of seventy-one leaders.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus said to all of his followers, <JESUS>\u201CIf you truly desire
        to be my disciple, you must disown your life completely, embrace my \u2018cross\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>as your own,</JESUS>  <JESUS>and surrender to my ways.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 9:23
        content: '  This could also mean being willing to suffer and die for Christ.    '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>For if you choose self-sacrifice, giving up your lives for
        my glory, you will discover true life. But if you choose to keep your lives
        for yourselves, you will lose what you try to keep.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>Even if you gained all the wealth and power of this world,
        and all the things it could offer you, yet lost your soul in the process,
        what good is that?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>So why then are you ashamed of being my disciple? Are you
        ashamed of the revelation-truth</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I give to
        you?</JESUS><JESUS>\u201CI, the Son of Man, will one day return in my radiant
        brightness, with the holy angels and in the splendor and majesty of my Father.
        On that day I will be ashamed of everyone who has been ashamed of me.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 9:26
        content: '  The Greek word is  .    '
    - name: '27: The True Glory of Jesus'
      title: The True Glory of Jesus
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI promise you this: there are some of you standing here
        right now who will not die until you have witnessed the presence and the
        power of God\u2019s kingdom realm.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:27
        content: "  Jesus prophesied of what was about to take place with Peter,
          Jacob (James), and John on the Mountain of Transforming Glory. This promise
          was fulfilled when they experienced the power of God\u2019s kingdom realm
          and the cloud of glory.    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Eight days later, Jesus took Peter, Jacob, and John and climbed a
        high mountain to pray. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: As he prayed, [[COMMENT(0)]] his face began to glow until a blinding
        glory streamed from him. A radiant glory illuminated his entire body. His
        brightness   became so intense that it made his clothing blinding white,
        as multiple flashes of lightning.
      comments:
      - number: 9:29
        content: "  This verse is a clear statement of the power of prayer to transform
          us and release God\u2019s glory in our life. It is impossible to overemphasize
          the importance of prayer in the life of a believer. Indeed, the present-day
          ministry of Jesus is to intercede for us on high ().      The Greek text
          says, \u201CThe appearance of his face was altered.\u201D The light shone
          through his clothing as his glorified body became brilliant with light.
          This is called Jesus\u2019 transfiguration.    "
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: 'All at once, two men appeared in glorious splendor: Moses and Elijah.
        [[COMMENT(0)]] They spoke with Jesus about his soon departure  from this
        world and the things the Father destined him to accomplish  in Jerusalem.'
      comments:
      - number: "9:30\u201331"
        content: "  Moses was the lawgiver, and Elijah was the notable and true prophet.
          Their appearance with Jesus on the Mountain of Transforming Glory points
          to the supremacy of Jesus over the Law and the prophets. See  .      The
          actual word in Greek is translated \u201Cexodus.\u201D      What a word
          is  ! Jesus was about to die in Jerusalem. We don\u2019t think of death
          as an accomplishment, but for Jesus, it was the marvelous accomplishment
          of salvation and victory for all who follow him.    "
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: 'All at once, two men appeared in glorious splendor: Moses and Elijah.
        [[COMMENT(0)]] They spoke with Jesus about his soon departure  from this
        world and the things the Father destined him to accomplish  in Jerusalem.'
      comments:
      - number: "9:30\u201331"
        content: "  Moses was the lawgiver, and Elijah was the notable and true prophet.
          Their appearance with Jesus on the Mountain of Transforming Glory points
          to the supremacy of Jesus over the Law and the prophets. See  .      The
          actual word in Greek is translated \u201Cexodus.\u201D      What a word
          is  ! Jesus was about to die in Jerusalem. We don\u2019t think of death
          as an accomplishment, but for Jesus, it was the marvelous accomplishment
          of salvation and victory for all who follow him.    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Peter and his companions had become very drowsy, but they became fully
        awake when they saw the glory and splendor of Jesus standing there and the
        two men with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "As Moses and Elijah were about to return to heaven, Peter impetuously
        blurted, \u201CMaster, this is amazing to see the three of you together!
        Why don\u2019t we stay here and set up three shelters: one for you, one for
        Moses, and one for Elijah?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:33
        content: '  Although Peter was not understanding the importance of this event,
          he did put Jesus first and left himself out altogether. Peter longed to
          remain in the glory he witnessed on the mountain.    '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'While Peter was still speaking, a radiant cloud of glory formed above
        them and overshadowed them. As the glory cloud enveloped them, they were
        struck with fear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then the voice of God thundered from within the cloud, \u201CThis
        is my Son, my Beloved One. [[COMMENT(0)]] Listen carefully to all he has
        to say.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 9:35
        content: "  Several Greek manuscripts have \u201Cmy Chosen One.\u201D     
          The Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit are all mentioned in this account.
          The Father spoke, the Son was transfigured, and the Spirit (in the form
          of the glory cloud) overshadowed those on the mountain.    "
    - name: '36: The Power of Faith'
      title: The Power of Faith
      number: 36
      content: "When the thunderous voice faded away and the cloud disappeared, Jesus
        was standing there alone. Peter, Jacob, and John were awestruck. But they
        didn\u2019t say a word to anyone about what they had seen."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The next day, a massive crowd was waiting at the foot of the mountain
        to meet them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "A man in the crowd shouted desperately, \u201CPlease, Teacher, I
        beg of you, do something about my son, my only son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "An evil spirit possesses him and makes him scream out in torment,
        and hardly ever leaves him alone. It throws him into convulsions and he foams
        at the mouth. When it finally does leave him, he\u2019s left with horrible
        bruises. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "I begged your disciples to drive it out of him, but they didn\u2019t
        have enough power to do it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CYou are an unbelieving people with
        no faith! You twist your lives with lies that have turned you away from doing
        the right things. How much longer should I remain here, offering you hope?\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]] Then he said to the man, <JESUS>\u201CBring your son to me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 9:41
        content: "  As translated from Aramaic text. Some translate this phrase \u201CHow
          long must I endure you?\u201D However, the Aramaic root word for \u201Cendure\u201D
          is  , which means \u201Chope\u201D or \u201Cgood news.\u201D    "
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "As the boy approached, the demon slammed him to the ground and threw
        him into violent convulsions. Jesus sternly commanded the demon to come out
        of the boy, and it left immediately. Jesus healed the boy of his injuries
        and returned him to his father, saying, <JESUS>\u201CHere is your son.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Everyone was awestruck and stunned to see such power and the majesty
        of God flow through Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Everyone marveled, trying to process what they had just witnessed.
        Jesus then turned to his disciples and said, <JESUS>\u201CListen carefully
        and let these words sink into your hearts. The Son of Man is about to be
        betrayed and surrendered to the authority of men.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: True Greatness'
      title: True Greatness
      number: 45
      content: But the disciples could not grasp the meaning of what he was saying,
        for it was a veiled mystery to them, and they were too embarrassed to ask
        him to explain it.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The disciples began to argue and became preoccupied over who would
        be the greatest one among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Fully aware of their innermost thoughts, Jesus called a little child
        to his side and said to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CIf you tenderly care for this little child</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>on my behalf, you are tenderly caring for me. And
        if you care for me, you are honoring my Father who sent me. The one who is
        least important in your eyes is actually the most important one of all.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 9:48
        content: '  The little child is representative of unimportant people in general.
          Treating the least with care and respect makes us truly great.    '
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "The disciple John said, \u201CMaster, we found someone casting out
        demons using your name and we tried to stop him, because he doesn\u2019t
        follow you as we do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "50: Jesus\u2019 Journey to Jerusalem"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Journey to Jerusalem"
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CYou shouldn\u2019t have hindered him,
        for anyone who is not against you is your friend.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:50
        content: '  Jealousy blinds our hearts. Nine disciples combined could not
          cast out a demon spirit (v.  ), and they were jealous of this one who did.    '
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Jesus let nothing distract him from departing for Jerusalem because
        the time for him to be lifted up [[COMMENT(0)]] drew near, and he was full
        of passion to complete his mission there. '
      comments:
      - number: 9:51
        content: "  \u201CLifted up\u201D refers to the cross, where Jesus was lifted
          up on a tree to bear the sins of all humankind. His exaltation into glory
          was through the sacrifice of his life on Calvary\u2019s cross. Nothing
          would turn him aside from being our Sin-Bearer and Redeemer.    "
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'So he sent messengers [[COMMENT(0)]] ahead of him as envoys to a
        village of the Samaritans. '
      comments:
      - number: 9:52
        content: "  The most literal translation is \u201CHe sent angels before his
          face.\u201D    "
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: But as they approached the village, the people turned them away. They
        would not allow Jesus to enter, for he was on his way to worship in Jerusalem.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 9:53
        content: '  The Samaritans had their own place of worship on Mount Gerizim,
          and they were hostile toward Jews, who wanted to worship in Jerusalem.
          There were many cultural, religious, and ethnic hostilities between Jews
          and Samaritans.    '
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "When the disciples Jacob and John realized what was happening, they
        returned to Jesus and said, \u201CLord, if you wanted to, you could command
        fire to fall down from heaven, just as Elijah did [[COMMENT(0)]] and destroy
        all these wicked people.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 9:54
        content: "  This sentence is translated from the Aramaic. The earliest Greek
          manuscripts do not include \u201Cjust like Elijah did.\u201D Some Greek
          texts state that the disciples asked, \u201CDo you want us to call down
          fire and destroy them?\u201D    "
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "Jesus rebuked them sharply, saying, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t you realize
        what spews from your hearts when you say that? The Son of Man did not come
        to destroy life, but to bring life to the earth.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:55
        content: '  Translated from Aramaic and a few Greek manuscripts. This pericope
          reveals the mercy of Jesus. Although the Samaritans refused entry to Jesus
          and his disciples, in the next chapter Jesus uses an example of a good
          Samaritan who cared for a stranger. Jesus saw in the Samaritan outcasts
          a redemptive future (). He knew the Father had the grace to change even
          the most stubborn individuals. An entire Samaritan village received Jesus
          through the witness of a woman (), and later, as recorded in the book of
          Acts, the entire region of the Samaritans received the gospel (). We can
          never give up on those who seem to be wayward.    '
    - name: '56: The Cost to Follow Jesus'
      title: The Cost to Follow Jesus
      number: 56
      content: So they went to another village instead.
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "On their way, someone came up to Jesus and said, \u201CI want to
        follow you wherever you go.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYes, but remember this: even animals
        in the field have holes in the ground to sleep in, and birds have their nests,
        but the Son of Man has no place to lay down his head.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "Jesus then turned to another and said, <JESUS>\u201CCome be my disciple.\u201D</JESUS>He
        replied, \u201CSomeday I will, Lord, but allow me first to fulfill my duty
        as a good son [[COMMENT(0)]] and wait until my father passes away.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 9:59
        content: "  The text is literally \u201CAllow me first to go and bury my
          father.\u201D This is an idiom for waiting until his father passed away.
          He wanted an inheritance in this life as his security.  "
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "Jesus told him, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t wait for your father\u2019s
        burial. Let those who are already dead wait for death. As for you, go and
        proclaim everywhere that God\u2019s kingdom has arrived.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "Still another said to him, \u201CLord, I want to follow you too.
        But first let me go home and say good-bye to my entire family.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CWhy do you keep looking back to your
        past and have second thoughts about following me? If you turn back you are
        not fit for God\u2019s kingdom.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Labor Shortage'
      title: Labor Shortage
      number: 1
      content: 'After this, the Lord Jesus formed thirty-five teams among the other
        disciples. Each team was two disciples, seventy in all, [[COMMENT(0)]] and
        he commissioned them to go ahead of him into every town he was about to visit. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:1
        content: "  A few Greek manuscripts have \u201Cseventy-two.\u201D The number
          seventy is a key numerical symbol in the Bible. Seventy nations are listed
          in  , seventy of Jacob\u2019s clan went into Egypt (), seventy palm trees
          refreshed God\u2019s people at Elim (), seventy elders served with Moses
          (), seventy princes are mentioned in  , seventy men sat on the council
          of the Sanhedrin, and Jesus sent out seventy apostles to preach the message
          of the kingdom.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He released them with these instructions:<JESUS>\u201CThe harvest
        is huge. But there are not enough harvesters to bring it in. As you go, plead
        with the Owner of the Harvest to send out</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] many more
        workers <JESUS>into his harvest fields.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 10:2
        content: '  This is the term used many times in the Gospels for driving out
          or casting out demons. The Lord of the Harvest must cast them forth. The
          Holy Spirit is the Director of the Harvest.    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>Now, off you go! I am sending you out even though you feel
        as vulnerable as lambs going into a pack of wolves.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>You won\u2019t need to take anything</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>with you\u2014trust in God alone. And don\u2019t get distracted from
        my purpose by anyone you might meet along the way.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 10:4
        content: "  The text states literally \u201CTake no money, no knapsack, no
          sandals.\u201D The implication is that they were to trust in God alone
          for all their needs to be met.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>\u201COnce you enter a house, speak to the people there and
        say, \u2018God\u2019s blessing of peace be upon this house!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>If a lover of peace</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>resides
        there, your peace will rest upon that household.</JESUS>    <JESUS>But if
        you are rejected, your blessing of peace will come back upon you.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 10:6
        content: "  Literally \u201Cson of peace,\u201D which is a way of saying,
          \u201Ca godly man.\u201D      Or as translated from the Aramaic, \u201CLet
          him rest upon your peace.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t shift from one house to another, but stay in one
        home during your time in that city. Eat and drink whatever they serve you.
        Receive their hospitality, for you are my harvester, and you deserve to be
        cared for.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen you enter into a new town, and you have been welcomed
        by its people, follow these rules: Eat</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>what
        is served you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 10:8
        content: "  This instruction to \u201Ceat what is served\u201D was given
          twice, for the Jewish dietary laws were not meant to be a hindrance in
          their ministry, nor were the disciples to demand certain foods.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>Heal the sick, and tell them all, \u2018God\u2019s kingdom
        has arrived and is now within your reach!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>But when you enter a city and they do not receive you, say
        to them publicly,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>\u2018We wipe from our feet the very dust of your streets
        as a testimony before you!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Understand this:
        God\u2019s kingdom came within your reach and yet you have rejected God\u2019s
        invitation!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 10:11
        content: '  See footnote on  .    '
    - name: '12: Jesus Condemns the Unrepentant Cities'
      title: Jesus Condemns the Unrepentant Cities
      number: 12
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CLet me say it clearly: on the day of
        judgment the wicked people of Sodom will have a lesser degree of judgment
        than the city that rejects you,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for Sodom did not have the
        opportunity that was given to them</JESUS><JESUS>.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHow disastrous it will be for the city of Korazin! How
        horrible for the city of Bethsaida! For if the powerful miracles that I performed
        in Korazin and Bethsaida had been done</JESUS>  <JESUS>in Tyre and Sidon</JESUS><JESUS>,
        they would have humbled themselves, repented, and turned from their sins.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>Tyre and Sidon</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will face a
        lesser degree of judgment than you will on the day of judgment.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 10:14
        content: '  Tyre and Sidon (present-day Lebanon) were two gentile cities
          on the Mediterranean coast that were known for their wickedness.    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>And Capernaum! Do you really think you\u2019ll be highly exalted
        because of the great things I have done there? No! You\u2019ll be brought
        down to the depths of hell</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>because of your
        rejection of me!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 10:15
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '16: The Seventy Return'
      title: The Seventy Return
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus concluded his instructions to the seventy with these words:
        <JESUS>\u201CRemember this: Whoever listens to your message is actually listening
        to me. And anyone who rejects you is rejecting me, and not only me but the
        one who sent me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When the seventy missionaries returned to Jesus, they were ecstatic
        with joy, telling him, \u201CLord, even the demons obeyed us when we commanded
        them in your name!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>While you were ministering</JESUS><JESUS>,
        I watched Satan topple until he fell suddenly from heaven like lightning
        to the ground.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>Now you understand that I have imparted to you my authority
        to trample over his kingdom. You will trample upon every demon before you
        and overcome every power</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Satan possesses.
        Absolutely nothing will harm you as you walk in this authority.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 10:19
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201Csnakes and scorpions,\u201D
          which are emblems of demonic powers.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>However, your real source of joy isn\u2019t merely that these
        spirits submit to your authority, but that your names are written in the
        journals of heaven and that you belong to God\u2019s kingdom. This is the
        true source of your authority.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Jesus, overflowing with the Holy Spirit\u2019s joy, exclaimed,
        <JESUS>\u201CFather, thank you, for you are Lord Supreme over heaven and
        earth! You have hidden the great revelation of this authority from those
        who are proud, those wise in their own eyes, and you have shared it with
        these who humbled themselves. Yes, Father. This is what pleases your heart:
        to give these things to those who are like trusting children.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CFather, you have entrusted me with all that you have.
        No one fully knows the Son except the Father. And no one fully knows the
        Father except the Son. But the Son is able to reveal the Father to anyone
        he chooses.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "When Jesus was alone with the Twelve, he said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou
        are privileged to see and hear all these things.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Loving God, Loving Others'
      title: Loving God, Loving Others
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Many kings and prophets of old longed to see these days of
        miracles that you\u2019ve been favored to see. They would have given everything
        to hear the revelation you\u2019ve been favored to hear. Yet they didn\u2019t
        get to see a glimpse or hear even a whisper.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Just then a religious scholar stood before Jesus in order to test
        his doctrines. He posed this question: \u201CTeacher, what requirement must
        I fulfill if I want to live forever in heaven?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CWhat do you read in the Law? How do you
        understand it?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The religious scholar answered, \u201CIt states, \u2018You must love
        the Lord God with all your heart, all your passion, all your energy, and
        your every thought. And you must love your neighbor as yourself.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CThat is correct. Now go and do exactly that
        and you will live.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Wanting to justify himself, he questioned Jesus further, saying,
        \u201CWhat do you mean by \u2018my neighbor\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CThere was once a</JESUS>  <JESUS>Jewish</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>man traveling from Jerusalem to Jericho when bandits
        robbed him along the way. They beat him severely, stripped him naked, and
        left him half dead.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 10:30
        content: '  Although the text does not describe him as Jewish, it is clearly
          implied in the context.    '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSoon, a Jewish priest walking down the same road came
        upon the wounded man. Seeing him from a distance, the priest crossed to the
        other side of the road and walked right past him, not turning to help him
        one bit.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CLater, a religious man, a Levite,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>came walking down the same road and likewise crossed to the other
        side to pass by the wounded man without stopping to help him.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 10:32
        content: '  The Levites were temple assistants, helping the priests ().    '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CFinally, another man, a Samaritan,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>came upon the bleeding man and was moved with tender compassion for
        him.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 10:33
        content: "  There was racial tension in those days between Jews and Samaritans.
          The Samaritans were considered to be a mixed race by the religious Jews.
          A Samaritan would be the most unlikely person to stop and help a Jewish
          man. The word    does not refer to people who lived in a geographical place,
          but is the Hebrew-Aramaic word  , which means \u201Ckeeper of the law.\u201D    "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>He stooped down and gave him first aid, pouring olive oil
        on his wounds,</JESUS>  <JESUS>disinfecting them</JESUS>  <JESUS>with wine,
        and bandaging them to stop the bleeding. Lifting him up, he placed him on
        his own donkey and brought him to an inn. Then he took him from his donkey
        and carried him to a room for the night.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>The next morning he took his own money from his wallet and
        gave it to the innkeeper with these words: \u2018Take care of him until I
        come back from my journey. If it costs more than this, I will repay you when
        I return.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 10:35
        content: '  Jesus is the Good Samaritan. He stoops down to touch us, heal
          us, lift us up, carry us on our journey, and pay our debts, and he promises
          to return and reward those who do his will.  '
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>So, now, tell me, which one of the three men who saw the wounded
        man proved to be the true neighbor?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Jesus Visits Martha and Mary'
      title: Jesus Visits Martha and Mary
      number: 37
      content: "The religious scholar responded, \u201CThe one who demonstrated kindness
        and mercy.\u201DJesus said, <JESUS>\u201CGo and do the same as he.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '38-39: '
      title: 
      number: 38-39
      content: 'As Jesus and the disciples continued on their journey, they came
        to a village where a woman welcomed Jesus into her home. Her name was Martha
        and she had a sister named Mary. Mary sat down attentively before the Master,
        absorbing every revelation he shared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38-39: '
      title: 
      number: 38-39
      content: 'As Jesus and the disciples continued on their journey, they came
        to a village where a woman welcomed Jesus into her home. Her name was Martha
        and she had a sister named Mary. Mary sat down attentively before the Master,
        absorbing every revelation he shared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But Martha became exasperated with finishing the numerous household
        chores in preparation for her guests, so she interrupted Jesus and said,
        \u201CLord, don\u2019t you think it\u2019s unfair that my sister left me
        to do all the work by myself? You should tell her to get up and help me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "The Lord answered her, <JESUS>\u201CMartha, my beloved Martha. Why
        are you upset and troubled, pulled away by all these many distractions?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>Mary has discovered the one thing most important by choosing
        to sit at my feet. She is undistracted, and I won\u2019t take this privilege
        from her.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Teaches about Prayer'
      title: Jesus Teaches about Prayer
      number: 1
      content: "One day, as Jesus was in prayer, one of his disciples came over to
        him as he finished and said, \u201CWould you teach us a model prayer that
        we can pray, just as John did for his disciples?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Jesus taught them this prayer: <JESUS>\u201COur heavenly Father,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>may the glory of your name be the center on which
        our life turns.</JESUS>    <JESUS>May your Holy Spirit come upon us and cleanse
        us.</JESUS>    <JESUS>Manifest your kingdom on earth.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:2
        content: "  Some Greek manuscripts read simply \u201CFather.\u201D The Aramaic
          is  .      An alternate reading of the Aramaic text. The Aramaic word for
          \u201Cname\u201D is    (or the Hebrew word,  ), a word with multiple meanings.
          It can also be translated as \u201Clight,\u201D \u201Csound,\u201D or \u201Catmosphere.\u201D
          Placing a light in an enclosed space, like a lantern, magnifies that light.
          This is the meaning here of God\u2019s name being made sacred and magnified
          as we focus our lives on him.      Translated from some of the earliest
          Greek manuscripts.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>And give us our needed bread for the coming day.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 11:3
        content: "  This is more than asking for food, for Jesus has taught us not
          to worry about the needs of our body. It is the request for tomorrow\u2019s
          living bread to come and feed us today.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>Forgive our sins as we ourselves release forgiveness to those
        who have wronged us. And rescue us every time we face tribulations.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:4
        content: "  Or \u201CDo not let us enter into ordeals.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jesus gave this illustration: <JESUS>\u201CImagine what would
        happen if you were to go to one of your friends in the middle of the night,
        pound on his door, and shout, \u2018Please! Do you have some food you can
        spare?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>A friend just arrived at my house unexpectedly and I have
        nothing to serve him.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:6
        content: '  In the culture of the day, it was important to honor every guest
          and provide a meal when they arrived.    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>But your friend says, \u2018Why are you bothering me? The
        door is locked and my family and I are all in bed. Do you expect me to get
        up and give you our food?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>I tell you\u2014because of your shameless persistence, even
        though it\u2019s the middle of the night, your friend will get up out of
        his bed and give you all that you need.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "<JESUS>So it is with your prayers. Ask and you\u2019ll receive. Seek
        and you\u2019ll discover. Knock on heaven\u2019s door, and it will one day
        open for you. Every persistent person will receive what he asks for. Every
        persistent seeker will discover what he needs. And everyone who knocks persistently
        will one day find an open door.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "<JESUS>So it is with your prayers. Ask and you\u2019ll receive. Seek
        and you\u2019ll discover. Knock on heaven\u2019s door, and it will one day
        open for you. Every persistent person will receive what he asks for. Every
        persistent seeker will discover what he needs. And everyone who knocks persistently
        will one day find an open door.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CLet me ask you this: Do you know of any father who would
        give his son a snake on a plate when he asked for a serving of fish?</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Of course not!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:11
        content: "  Some manuscripts substitute the word \u201Cfish\u201D with \u201Cloaf\u201D
          (bread) and the word \u201Csnake\u201D with \u201Ca stone.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>Do you know of any father who would give his daughter a spider
        when she had asked for an egg? Of course not!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jesus Responds to Controversy'
      title: Jesus Responds to Controversy
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>If imperfect parents know how to lovingly take care of their
        children and give them what they need, how much more will the perfect heavenly
        Father give the Holy Spirit\u2019s fullness when his children ask him.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "One day a crowd gathered around Jesus, and among them was a man who
        was mute. Jesus drove out of the man the spirit that made him unable to speak.
        When the demon left him, the mute man\u2019s tongue was loosed and immediately
        he was able to speak. The stunned crowd saw it all and marveled in amazement
        over this miracle! "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But there were some in the crowd who protested, saying, \u201CHe
        casts out demons by the power of Satan, [[COMMENT(0)]] the demon king.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 11:15
        content: "  The word used here is  , which was an Aramaic word for \u201Cthe
          prince of devils,\u201D whom the Philistines worshiped. In Hebrew    means
          \u201Clord of the flies.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Others were skeptical and tried to persuade Jesus to perform a spectacular
        display of power to prove that he was the Messiah.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus, well aware of their every thought, said to them, <JESUS>\u201CEvery
        kingdom that is split against itself is doomed to fail and will eventually
        collapse.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>If it is true that Satan casts out his own demons through
        me, how could his kingdom remain intact?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>If Satan gives me the power to cast out his demons, who is
        it that gives your exorcists</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>their power?
        Let them become your judges! Go, ask them, and they will tell you.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 11:19
        content: "  Literally \u201Cyour sons,\u201D which is a figure of speech
          for their followers.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>But if I am casting out demons by God\u2019s mighty power,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>God\u2019s kingdom is now released upon you\u2014</JESUS><JESUS>but
        you still reject it</JESUS>!"
      comments:
      - number: 11:20
        content: "  The text literally states \u201Cin the finger of God,\u201D a
          Hebrew phrase denoting God\u2019s power. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen a strong man, with many weapons, guards his palace,
        his possessions are safe.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>But when one stronger than he comes to attack and overpower
        him, the stronger one will empty the arsenal in which he trusted. The conqueror
        will ransack his kingdom and distribute all the spoils of victory.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: <JESUS>Whoever is not on my side is against me, and whoever does not
        gather the spoils with me will be forever scattered.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen a demon is cast out of a person, it goes to wander
        in a waterless realm, searching for rest. But finding no place to rest, it
        says, \u2018I will go back and reoccupy the body I left.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>When it returns, it finds the person like a house swept clean
        and made tidy,</JESUS>  <JESUS>but empty.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 11:25
        content: "  Implied in the text is the truth that if a person is delivered
          from a demon but does not receive Christ and become filled with him, that
          individual\u2019s condition can become even worse. True conversion fills
          a life with Christ and his Spirit.    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>Then it goes and enlists seven demons more evil than itself,
        and they all enter and possess the person, leaving that one in a much worse
        state than before.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:26
        content: "  Christ\u2019s power is still available for all. Even Mary Magdalene
          had seven demons cast out of her. See  .    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "While he was saying all this, a woman shouted from the crowd, \u201CGod
        bless the one who gave you birth and nursed you as a child!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: The Miracle Sign of Jonah the Prophet'
      title: The Miracle Sign of Jonah the Prophet
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYes,\u201D</JESUS> said Jesus, <JESUS>\u201Cbut God
        will bless all who listen to the word of God and carefully obey everything
        they hear.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "As the crowds continued to swell, Jesus went on to say, <JESUS>\u201CHow
        evil is this generation! When you demand a mighty display of power simply
        to prove who I am,</JESUS>  <JESUS>you demonstrate your unbelief</JESUS><JESUS>.
        The only sign you will see will be a repeat of the miracle of Jonah.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: <JESUS>In the same way Jonah became a sign to the people of Nineveh,
        so the Son of Man will be a sign to this generation.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 11:30
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Ctribe.\u201D See v.  . The Ninevites were
          a different Semitic tribe from the Jews.    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe Queen of Sheba</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will
        rise up on the day of judgment to accuse and condemn this generation</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>for its unbelief</JESUS><JESUS>. She journeyed from a far and distant
        land just to listen to the wisdom of King Solomon. One greater than Solomon
        speaks with you today,</JESUS>  <JESUS>but you refuse to listen.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:31
        content: "  Literally \u201Cthe queen of the south.\u201D See  . Sheba is
          modern-day Yemen.    "
    - name: '32: Revelation-Light'
      title: Revelation-Light
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>Yes, the people of Nineveh will also rise up on the day of
        judgment to accuse and condemn this generation.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>For they all repented when they heard the preaching of Jonah, but
        you refuse to repent. Yet there is one greater than Jonah who is preaching
        to you today.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 11:32
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Ctribe.\u201D The Ninevites were of Semitic
          origin, and although they were pagans, after the preaching of one prophet
          they converted. The people of Israel had many prophets throughout their
          history, and the greatest prophet of all was now preaching to them, yet
          they refused to listen.    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CNo one would think of lighting a lamp and then hiding
        it in the basement where no one would benefit. A lamp belongs on a lampstand,
        where all who enter may see its light.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>The eyes of your spirit allow revelation-light</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>to enter into your being. When your heart is open the light floods
        in.</JESUS>    <JESUS>But when your heart is hard and closed, the light cannot
        penetrate and darkness takes its place.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 11:34
        content: "  The teachings of Jesus are the \u201Crevelation-light\u201D referred
          to here.      Or \u201CThe eye is like a lamp to your body.\u201D The literal
          Greek text reads \u201CYour eye is the lamp of your body. If your eye is
          healthy, your whole body is full of light; but if it is sick, your body
          is full of darkness.\u201D The eye becomes a metaphor for spiritual perception.
          The body is our spirit. The lamp is Jesus\u2019 teachings. The darkness
          is formed by the lies and opinions that blind us. These metaphors have
          been made explicit.    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>Open your heart and consider my words. Watch out that you
        do not mistake your opinions for revelation-light!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Jesus Warns Hypocrites'
      title: Jesus Warns Hypocrites
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>If your spirit burns with light, fully illuminated with no
        trace of darkness, you will be a shining lamp, reflecting rays of truth by
        the way you live.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '37-38: '
      title: 
      number: 37-38
      content: After Jesus finished saying these things, a Pharisee asked him to
        come for a meal at his home. When everyone had been seated at the table,
        the religious leader noticed that Jesus had not performed the cleansing ritual
        [[COMMENT(0)]] before he began eating. He was shocked.
      comments:
      - number: "11:37\u201338"
        content: '  This was not required by the law of Moses, but was a rule imposed
          by the Pharisees.    '
    - name: '37-38: '
      title: 
      number: 37-38
      content: After Jesus finished saying these things, a Pharisee asked him to
        come for a meal at his home. When everyone had been seated at the table,
        the religious leader noticed that Jesus had not performed the cleansing ritual
        [[COMMENT(0)]] before he began eating. He was shocked.
      comments:
      - number: "11:37\u201338"
        content: '  This was not required by the law of Moses, but was a rule imposed
          by the Pharisees.    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "The Lord said, <JESUS>\u201CYou Pharisees are like those who will
        wipe clean only the outside of a cup or bowl,</JESUS>  <JESUS>leaving the
        inside filthy.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>You are foolish to ignore the greed and wickedness within
        you! Shouldn\u2019t the one who cleans the outside also clean the inside?</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:40
        content: '  Translated from the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: <JESUS>If you free your heart of greed, show compassion and true generosity
        to the poor, you will have more than clean hands; you will be clean within.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou Pharisees are hypocrites!</JESUS>  <JESUS>For you
        are obsessed with peripheral issues</JESUS><JESUS>, like paying meticulous
        tithes on the smallest herbs that grow in your gardens.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>Of course, these matters you should do, but when you unjustly cheat
        others, you ignore the most important duty of all: to walk in the love of
        God.</JESUS>    <JESUS>Readjust</JESUS>  <JESUS>your values and place first
        things first.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 11:42
        content: "  Literally \u201CYou pay tithes even on mint and dill and every
          other garden herb.\u201D      See  .    "
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou Pharisees are hypocrites! You love to be honored
        before others with titles of respect, seeking public recognition,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>aspiring to seem more important than others.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:43
        content: "  Literally \u201Cgreeted with respect in the marketplaces.\u201D     
          The Aramaic text states, \u201CYou aspire to leadership of the synagogues.\u201D    "
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou Pharisees, what hypocrites! Your true character
        is hidden, like an unmarked grave that hides the corruption inside, defiling
        all who come in contact with you.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:44
        content: '  A strictly religious Jew was forbidden to touch a dead body or
          walk over a grave. It was common to whitewash the grave so no one would
          walk on it and be ceremonially defiled. Jesus taught that people who followed
          the example of the Pharisees would become morally unclean.    '
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Just then a specialist in interpreting religious law blurted out,
        \u201CTeacher, don\u2019t you realize that your words insult us?!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CYou are also hypocrites, you experts
        of the law! You crush people beneath the burden of obeying impossible religious
        regulations, yet you would never even think of doing them yourselves.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:46
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201CYou compel men to carry burdens
          that you yourselves do not touch.\u201D    "
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>What hypocrites! You build monuments to honor the prophets
        of old, yet it was your murdering ancestors who killed them.</JESUS>  <JESUS>The
        only prophet you\u2019ll honor is a dead one!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "<JESUS>In fact, by erecting monuments to the prophets your ancestors
        killed, you demonstrate your agreement with those murderers and bear witness
        to their deeds.</JESUS>  <JESUS>You\u2019re no better than they!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "<JESUS>That is why God\u2019s wisdom is proclaiming: \u2018I will
        send to them apostles and prophets though some they will murder and others
        they will persecute.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CGod will hold this generation accountable for every
        drop of blood of every murdered prophet shed from the beginning of time until
        now,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: <JESUS>from the blood of Abel, who was killed by his brother, to the
        blood of Zechariah,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>who was murdered in the
        middle of the temple court. Yes, I tell you, you will be responsible for
        it all.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 11:51
        content: '  See  . Second Chronicles is the last book in the Hebrew order
          of the Old Testament. So the implied time frame is from Genesis throughout
          the period of the Old Testament.  '
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou are nothing but hypocrites, you experts of religion!
        You take away from others the key that opens the door to the house of knowledge.
        Not only do you lock the door and refuse to enter, but you also do your best
        to keep others from the truth.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '53-54: '
      title: 
      number: 53-54
      content: "All that Jesus said enraged the religious leaders and experts of
        the law and they began to oppose him furiously. They harassed Jesus all the
        way out the door, spewing out their hostility, arguing over everything he
        said\u2014wanting nothing more than to find a reason to entrap him with his
        own words."
      comments: []
    - name: '53-54: '
      title: 
      number: 53-54
      content: "All that Jesus said enraged the religious leaders and experts of
        the law and they began to oppose him furiously. They harassed Jesus all the
        way out the door, spewing out their hostility, arguing over everything he
        said\u2014wanting nothing more than to find a reason to entrap him with his
        own words."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Warns against Hypocrisy'
      title: Jesus Warns against Hypocrisy
      number: 1
      content: "By now a crowd of many thousands had gathered around Jesus. So many
        people pushed to be near him, they began to trample one another.Jesus turned
        to his disciples and warned them, <JESUS>\u201CBeware of the hypocrisy of
        the Pharisees. It permeates everything they do and teach, like leaven.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:1
        content: "  The Aramaic adds \u201Cserving their own interests.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>Everything hidden and covered up will soon be exposed. For
        the facade is falling down, and nothing will be kept secret for long.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: <JESUS>Whatever you have spoken in private will be public knowledge,
        and what you have whispered secretly behind closed doors will be broadcast
        far and wide for all to hear.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CListen, my beloved friends, don\u2019t fear those who
        may want to take your life but can do nothing more. It\u2019s true that they
        may kill your body, but they have no power over your soul.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: <JESUS>The one you must fear is God, for he has both the power to
        take your life and the authority to cast your soul into hell.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>Yes, the only one you need to fear is God.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 12:5
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201Cthe Valley of Hinnom.\u201D
          This was a valley along the south side of Jerusalem where excrement and
          rubbish were burned continually. It became a Jewish metaphor for the place
          of eternal punishment.    "
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhat is the value of your soul to God? Could your worth
        be defined by any amount of money? God doesn\u2019t abandon or forget even
        the small sparrow he has made. How then could he forget or abandon you? What
        about the seemingly minor issues of your life? Do they matter to God? Of
        course they do! So you never need to worry, for you are more valuable to
        God than anything else in this world.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "12:6\u20137"
        content: "  This translation has chosen to make explicit the figures of speech
          and metaphors of these verses. The literal Greek text reads \u201CDo not
          five sparrows sell for two copper coins? Not one is overlooked before God.
          Indeed, the very hairs of your head are numbered. Stop fearing\u2014you
          are more valuable than many sparrows.\u201D    "
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhat is the value of your soul to God? Could your worth
        be defined by any amount of money? God doesn\u2019t abandon or forget even
        the small sparrow he has made. How then could he forget or abandon you? What
        about the seemingly minor issues of your life? Do they matter to God? Of
        course they do! So you never need to worry, for you are more valuable to
        God than anything else in this world.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "12:6\u20137"
        content: "  This translation has chosen to make explicit the figures of speech
          and metaphors of these verses. The literal Greek text reads \u201CDo not
          five sparrows sell for two copper coins? Not one is overlooked before God.
          Indeed, the very hairs of your head are numbered. Stop fearing\u2014you
          are more valuable than many sparrows.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI can assure you of this: If you freely declare in public
        that I am the Son of Man, the Messiah, then I will freely declare to all
        the angels of God that you are mine.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>But if you publicly pretend that you don\u2019t know me, I
        will deny you before the angels of God.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>If anyone speaks evil of me, the Son of Man, that one can
        be forgiven. But if anyone speaks scornfully against the Holy Spirit, it
        will never be forgiven.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>And remember this: When people publicly accuse you</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and forcefully drag you before the religious leaders
        and authorities, do not be troubled. Don\u2019t worry about defending yourself
        or how to answer their accusations.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:11
        content: "  The Greek text adds \u201Cin the synagogues.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: Jesus Condemns Greed'
      title: Jesus Condemns Greed
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>Simply be confident and allow the Spirit of Wisdom access
        to your heart, and in that very moment he will reveal what you are to say
        to them.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Just then someone spoke up from the crowd and said, \u201CMaster,
        you should compel my older brother to divide the family inheritance and give
        me my fair share!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Jesus answered, [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u201CMy friend, who made
        me a judge or arbitrator over you?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 12:14
        content: '  In the Jewish culture of that day, rabbis would be asked to mediate
          disputes such as this. However, the man did not want mediation but representation.    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Speaking to the people, Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CBe alert and
        guard your heart from greed and from always wishing for what you don\u2019t
        have. For your life can never be measured by the amount of things you possess.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus then gave them this illustration: <JESUS>\u201CA wealthy land
        owner had a farm that produced bumper crops. Every year the harvest was so
        great it filled his barns to overflowing!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>He thought, \u2018What should I do now that every barn is
        full and I have nowhere else to store more?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I know what I\u2019ll do! I\u2019ll tear down the barns and
        build one massive barn to hold all my grain and goods.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Then I can just sit back, surrounded with comfort and ease.
        I\u2019ll enjoy life with no worries at all.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CGod said to him, \u2018What a fool you are to trust
        in your riches and not in me! This very night the messengers of death</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will demand to take your life. Then who will get all
        the wealth you have stored up for yourself?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:20
        content: "  The Greek text is simply \u201Cthey.\u201D    "
    - name: "21: Don\u2019t Worry"
      title: "Don\u2019t Worry"
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>The same thing will happen to all those who fill up their
        lives with everything but God.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Jesus taught his disciples, saying, <JESUS>\u201CListen to me. Never
        let anxiety enter your hearts. Never worry about any of your needs, such
        as food or clothing.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>For your life is infinitely more than just the food you eat
        or the clothing you wear.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Take the carefree birds as your example. Do you ever see them
        worry? They neither grow their own food nor put it in a storehouse for later.
        Yet God takes care of every one of them, feeding each of them out of</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>the abundance of</JESUS>  <JESUS>his love and goodness. Isn\u2019t
        your life more precious to God than a bird?</JESUS>  <JESUS>Be carefree in
        the care of God!</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CDoes worry add anything to your life? Can it add one
        more year, or even one day?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>So if worrying adds nothing, but actually subtracts from your
        life, why would you worry about God\u2019s care of you?</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThink about the lilies. They grow and become beautiful,
        not because they work hard or strive to clothe themselves. Yet not even Solomon,
        wearing his kingly garments of splendor, could be compared to a field of
        lilies.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>If God can clothe the fields and meadows with grass and flowers,
        can he not clothe you as well, O&nbsp;struggling one with so many doubts?</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 12:28
        content: "  This Greek word means \u201Clittle faiths.\u201D    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>I repeat: Don\u2019t let worry enter your life. Live above
        the anxious cares about your personal needs.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>People everywhere seem to worry about making a living, but
        your heavenly Father knows your every need and will take care of you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '<JESUS>As you passionately seek his kingdom, above all else, he will
        supply your needs.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>So don\u2019t ever be afraid, dearest friends! Your loving
        Father joyously gives you his kingdom with all its promises!</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CNow, go and sell what you have and give to those in
        need; you will be making deposits in your account in heaven, an account that
        will never be taken from you. Your gifts will become a secure and unfailing
        treasure, deposited in heaven forever.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Be Ready'
      title: Be Ready
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>Where you deposit your treasure, that is where you fix your
        thoughts\u2014and your heart will long to be there also.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBe prepared for action</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>at
        a moment\u2019s notice.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:35
        content: "  The Greek is literally \u201CLet your loins be girded and keep
          your lamps burning.\u201D    "
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>Be like servants anticipating their master\u2019s return from
        a wedding celebration. They are ready at a moment\u2019s notice to unlock
        and open the door for him.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>What great joy is ahead for those who stay awake and wait
        for their Master\u2019s return! He himself will become their servant and
        wait on them.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>He may appear at midnight or even later, but what great joy
        for the awakened ones whenever he comes!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>Of course, if they knew ahead of time the hour of their master\u2019s
        appearing, they would be alert, just as they would be ready if they knew
        ahead of time that a thief was coming to break into their house.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: The Faithful Servant'
      title: The Faithful Servant
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>So keep being alert and ready at all times. For I promise
        you that the Son of Man will surprise you and appear</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>when you don\u2019t expect him.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 12:40
        content: "  The Greek word can also be translated \u201Cbecome.\u201D    "
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CLord,\u201D Peter asked, \u201Cdoes this apply only to the
        twelve of us, or is it for everyone else as well?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "The Lord replied, <JESUS>\u201CA master will delegate authority in
        his house to a trustworthy and thoughtful manager who understands his master\u2019s
        desires. And the household manager will serve others what they need at exactly
        the right time.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43-44: '
      title: 
      number: 43-44
      content: <JESUS>And whenever his master returns, he will find that his servant
        has served him well. I promise you, the master will reward him generously
        and he will be placed as an overseer of everything he owns.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '43-44: '
      title: 
      number: 43-44
      content: <JESUS>And whenever his master returns, he will find that his servant
        has served him well. I promise you, the master will reward him generously
        and he will be placed as an overseer of everything he owns.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBut what if that servant says in his heart, \u2018My
        master delays his coming, and who knows when he will return?\u2019 Because
        of the delay, the servant elevates himself and mistreats those in his master\u2019s
        household. Instead of caring for the ones he was appointed to serve, he abuses
        the other servants, both men and women. He throws drunken parties for his
        friends and gives himself over to every pleasure.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: <JESUS>Let me tell you what will happen to him. His master will suddenly
        return at a time that shocks him, and he will remove the abusive, selfish
        servant from his position of trust. The master will punish him and assign
        him a portion with the unbelievers.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CEvery servant who knows what pleases his master yet
        does not make himself ready and refuses to put his master\u2019s will to
        action will receive many punishing blows.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: Jesus Brings Fire to the Earth'
      title: Jesus Brings Fire to the Earth
      number: 48
      content: "<JESUS>Every servant who does not know</JESUS>  <JESUS>his master\u2019s
        will</JESUS>  <JESUS>and unwittingly does what is wrong will receive a less
        severe punishment. For those who have received a greater revelation from
        their master are required a greater obedience. And those who have been entrusted
        with great responsibility will be held more responsible to their master.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI have come to set the earth on fire, and how I wish
        it were already ablaze with</JESUS>  <JESUS>fiery passion for God!</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:49
        content: "  Some scholars believe this fire that Jesus came to bring is judgment.
          But Jesus did not come to judge the world but to save it (). He wished
          not for judgment but mercy to grip the hearts of God\u2019s people. He
          interceded for those who crucified him.    "
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "<JESUS>But first I must be immersed into the baptism</JESUS>  <JESUS>of
        God\u2019s judgment,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and I am consumed with
        passion as I await its fulfillment.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:50
        content: "  The implication of the context is that Jesus was drawing closer
          to his time of experiencing God\u2019s judgment for our sins on the cross.
          It is a \u201Cbaptism\u201D of judgment that we deserved.    "
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t think for a moment that I came to grant peace and
        harmony to everyone. No, my arrival will change everything and create hostility
        among you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: '<JESUS>From now on, even family members will be divided over me and
        will choose sides</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>one against another.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 12:52
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201CAmong five in one house, three
          will be against two and two will be against three.\u201D    "
    - name: '53: Discerning the Time'
      title: Discerning the Time
      number: 53
      content: "<JESUS>Fathers will be divided from sons and sons from fathers; mothers
        will be divided from daughters and daughters from mothers; mothers-in-law
        will be against brides and brides against mothers-in-law\u2014all because
        of me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Jesus then said to the crowds gathered around him, <JESUS>\u201CWhen
        you see a cloud forming in the west, don\u2019t you say, \u2018A storm is
        brewing\u2019? And then it arrives.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "<JESUS>And when you feel the south wind blowing, you say, \u2018A
        heat wave is on the way.\u2019 And so it happens.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "<JESUS>What hypocrites!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>You are such
        experts at forecasting the weather, but you are totally unwilling to understand</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>the spiritual significance of</JESUS>  <JESUS>the time you\u2019re
        living in.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 12:56
        content: "  There is an amazing play on words found in the Aramaic text.
          The word translated \u201Chypocrites\u201D is literally \u201Caccepter
          of faces.\u201D The Aramaic states that the Pharisees looked at the \u201Cface\u201D
          of the sky and the \u201Cfaces\u201D of men, living superficially, not
          seeing what was happening spiritually around them.  "
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou can\u2019t even judge for yourselves what is good
        and right.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen you are guilty of wrong-doing, it is better to
        agree with your adversary and settle your dispute before you have to go before
        a judge. If not, your adversary may drag you into court, and the judge may
        find you guilty and</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "<JESUS>throw you into prison until you have paid off your fine entirely.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Need for True Repentance'
      title: The Need for True Repentance
      number: 1
      content: Some of those in the crowd informed Jesus that Pilate had slaughtered
        some Galilean Jews [[COMMENT(0)]] while they were offering sacrifices at
        the temple, mixing their blood with the sacrifices they were offering.
      comments:
      - number: 13:1
        content: '  It is likely that Pilate viewed these Jews as rebellious to his
          rule. This was indeed an atrocious act by Pilate.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jesus turned and asked them, <JESUS>\u201CDo you believe that the
        slaughtered Galileans were the worst sinners of all the Galileans?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>No, they weren\u2019t! So listen to me, unless you all repent,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you will perish as they did.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:3
        content: "  The Greek term for repentance means \u201Cto change your mind
          and amend your ways.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>What about the eighteen who perished when the tower of Siloam</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>fell upon them? Do you really think that they were
        more guilty than all of the others in Jerusalem?</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 13:4
        content: '  Siloam was the name of a pool or reservoir for the city of Jerusalem
          near the junction of the south and east walls of the city.    '
    - name: '5: The Parable of the Barren Tree'
      title: The Parable of the Barren Tree
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>No, they weren\u2019t, and unless you repent, you too will
        all eternally perish, just as they did.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Jesus told them this parable: <JESUS>\u201CThere was a man who
        planted a fig tree in his orchard. But every time he came to gather fruit
        from his tree he found none, for it was barren.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>So he said to his gardener, \u2018For the last three years
        I\u2019ve come to gather figs from my tree but it remains fruitless. What
        a waste! Go ahead and cut it down!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBut the gardener protested, \u2018Sir, we should leave
        it one more year. Let me fertilize and cultivate it, then let\u2019s see
        if it will produce fruit.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath Day'
      title: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath Day
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>If it doesn\u2019t bear figs by next year, we\u2019ll cut
        it down.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 13:9
        content: "  This parable was an obvious picture of the nation of Israel.
          The owner was the Father and the gardener was Jesus, who had come to them
          and for three years had longed to have true spiritual fruit from his spiritual
          vine (). The warning is that Israel would be cut down if the people did
          not repent and prove it by a changed life. The purpose of the parable was
          to warn people that they were in their last year of God\u2019s grace toward
          them.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'One Sabbath day, while Jesus was teaching in the synagogue, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: he encountered a seriously handicapped woman. She was crippled and
        had been doubled over for eighteen years. Her condition was caused by a demonic
        spirit of bondage [[COMMENT(0)]] that had left her unable to stand up straight.
      comments:
      - number: 13:11
        content: "  Literally \u201Cspirit of weakness.\u201D    "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "When Jesus saw her condition, he called her to him and gently laid
        his hands on her. Then he said, <JESUS>\u201CDear woman, you are free. I
        release you forever from this crippling spirit.\u201D</JESUS> Instantly she
        stood straight and tall and overflowed with glorious praise to God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: "When Jesus saw her condition, he called her to him and gently laid
        his hands on her. Then he said, <JESUS>\u201CDear woman, you are free. I
        release you forever from this crippling spirit.\u201D</JESUS> Instantly she
        stood straight and tall and overflowed with glorious praise to God!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Jewish leader who was in charge of the synagogue was infuriated
        over Jesus healing on the Sabbath day. \u201CSix days you are to work,\u201D
        he shouted angrily to the crowd. \u201COn those days you should come here
        for healing, but not on the seventh day!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Lord replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou hypocrites! Don\u2019t you care
        for your animals on the Sabbath, untying your ox or donkey from the stall
        and leading it away to water?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>If you do this for your animals, what\u2019s wrong with allowing
        this beloved daughter of Abraham,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>who has
        been bound by Satan for eighteen long years, to be untied and set free on
        a Sabbath day?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 13:16
        content: "  The Jews spoke frequently about the sons of Abraham or an individual
          being a son of Abraham, but Jesus was the first to use this phrase \u201Cdaughter
          of Abraham,\u201D giving women equal value.    "
    - name: '17: Parables of Jesus'
      title: Parables of Jesus
      number: 17
      content: When they heard this, his critics were completely humiliated. But
        the crowds shouted with joy over the glorious things Jesus was doing among
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jesus taught them this parable: <JESUS>\u201CHow can I describe God\u2019s
        kingdom?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>God\u2019s kingdom is like the smallest seed that one might
        plant in a garden. When it grows, it becomes a huge tree, with so many spreading
        branches that various birds make nests there.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 13:19
        content: "  See  . The obvious meaning of this parable is that God\u2019s
          kingdom will begin small but it will expand, grow, and mature. People from
          every nation will come and make a \u201Cnest\u201D in the kingdom of God.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jesus taught them another parable: <JESUS>\u201CHow can I describe
        God\u2019s kingdom?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Way of the Kingdom'
      title: The Way of the Kingdom
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>God\u2019s kingdom is like something as small as yeast that
        a woman kneads into a large amount of dough. It works unseen until it permeates</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>the entire batch and the loaf rises high.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 13:21
        content: '  This parable teaches that something small can impact and penetrate
          something great. It highlights the pervading influence of virtue and truth.
          A transformation takes place when the hidden yet pervasive kingdom impacts
          every part of culture and society around us.    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Jesus ministered from village to village, [[COMMENT(0)]] making his
        way to Jerusalem and teaching the people as he went. '
      comments:
      - number: 13:22
        content: '  Jesus now visits the places where his disciples had already been.
          See  .    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "A bystander asked him, \u201CLord, will only a few have eternal life?\u201DJesus
        said to the crowd, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThere is a great cost</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for
        anyone to enter through the narrow doorway into God\u2019s kingdom. I tell
        you, many will want to enter but won\u2019t be able to.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:24
        content: "  The Greek word used here is actually \u201Cagonize.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>Once the head of the house has shut and locked the door, it
        will be too late. Even if you stand outside knocking, begging to enter, and
        saying, \u2018Lord, Lord, open the door for us,\u2019 he will say to you,
        \u2018I don\u2019t know who you are.</JESUS>  <JESUS>You are not a part of
        my family</JESUS><JESUS>.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThen you will reply, \u2018But Lord, we dined with you
        and walked with you as you taught us.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>And he will reply, \u2018Don\u2019t you understand? I don\u2019t
        know who you are, for you are not a part of my family. I will not let you
        in. Now, go away from me! For you are all disloyal to me and do evil.\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 13:27
        content: "  This is quoted from  . Though they were acquaintances, they had
          not responded to his message with repentance. The word    is taken from
          the Aramaic. The question to ask is not simply, \u201CWill the saved be
          few?\u201D (v.  ) but rather, \u201CWill it be you?\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou will experience great weeping and great anguish
        when you see Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, along with all the prophets of Israel,
        enjoying God\u2019s kingdom while you yourselves are barred from entering.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>You will see people streaming from the four corners of the
        earth, accepting the invitation to feast in God\u2019s kingdom realm,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>while you are outside looking in.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jesus\u2019 Sorrow for Jerusalem"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Sorrow for Jerusalem"
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>And take note of this: Some are despised and viewed as the
        least important now, but one day the master will place them at the head of
        the line. And some whom you view as \u2018elite\u2019 today will become the
        least important then.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Just then some Jewish religious leaders came to Jesus to urge him
        to flee from that place because Herod was out to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CGo and tell that deceiver</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>that I will continue to cast out demons and heal the
        sick today and tomorrow, and on the third day I will bring my work to perfection.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:32
        content: "  Or \u201Cfox.\u201D    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '<JESUS>For everyone knows I am safe until I come to Jerusalem, for
        that is where all the prophets have been killed.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>O&nbsp;City of Jerusalem, you are the city who murders your
        prophets! You are the city who pelts to death with stones the very messengers</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>sent to deliver you! So many times I have longed to
        gather your wayward children together around me, as a hen gathers her chicks
        under her wings\u2014but you were too stubborn to let me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:34
        content: "  Or \u201Capostles.\u201D    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>Now it is too late, since your house will be left in ruins.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>You will not see me again until you are able to say,
        \u2018We welcome the one who comes to us sent in the name of the Lord.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:35
        content: '  See  .      See  .  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath'
      title: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath
      number: 1
      content: 'One Sabbath, Jesus was on his way to dine with a prominent Jewish
        religious leader for a festive meal. Everyone was watching him to see if
        he would heal anyone on the Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Just then, standing right in front of him was a man with his limbs
        suffering from edema.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus asked the experts of the law and the Pharisees who were present,
        <JESUS>\u201CDoes the law permit a man to heal on the Sabbath day? Is it
        right or wrong?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: No one dared answer, so Jesus turned to the sick man, released healing
        to him, and sent him on his way.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus said to them all, <JESUS>\u201CIf one of your children or one
        of your animals fell into a well, wouldn\u2019t you do all you could to rescue
        them even on the Sabbath?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Humility and Hospitality'
      title: Humility and Hospitality
      number: 6
      content: "There was nothing they could say\u2014all were silenced."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When Jesus noticed how the guests for the meal were all vying for
        the seats of honor, he shared this story with the guests around the table:'
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen you are invited to an important social function,
        don\u2019t be quick to sit near the head of the table, choosing for yourself
        a seat of honor. What will happen to you when someone arrives who is more
        distinguished than you?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>The host will bring him over to where you are sitting and
        ask for your seat, saying in front of all the guests, \u2018You\u2019re in
        the wrong place. Please give this person your seat.\u2019 Disgraced, you
        will have to take whatever seat is left.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>Instead, when you\u2019re invited to a banquet, you should
        choose to sit in the lowest place.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>When your
        host comes and sees you there, he may say, \u2018My friend, come with me
        and let me seat you in a better place.\u2019 Then, in front of all the other
        guests at the banquet, he will honor you by seating you in the place of highest
        respect.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 14:10
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CRemember this: everyone with a lofty opinion of who
        he is and who seeks to raise himself up will be publicly humbled. And everyone
        with a modest opinion of who he is and chooses to humble himself will be
        raised up before all.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jesus turned to his host and said, <JESUS>\u201CWhen you throw
        a banquet, don\u2019t just invite your friends, relatives, or rich neighbors\u2014for
        it is likely they will return the favor.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "<JESUS>It is better to invite those who never get an invitation.
        If you invite the poor to your banquet, along with the outcast, the handicapped,
        and the blind\u2014those who could never repay you the favor, then you will
        experience a great blessing in this life, and at the resurrection of the
        godly you will receive a full reward.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "<JESUS>It is better to invite those who never get an invitation.
        If you invite the poor to your banquet, along with the outcast, the handicapped,
        and the blind\u2014those who could never repay you the favor, then you will
        experience a great blessing in this life, and at the resurrection of the
        godly you will receive a full reward.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When they heard this, one of the dinner guests said to Jesus, \u201CSomeday
        God will have a kingdom feast, [[COMMENT(0)]] and how happy and privileged
        will be the ones who get to share in that joy!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 14:15
        content: "  The guest at the dinner assumed God\u2019s kingdom was coming
          one day, but Jesus\u2019 parable explained that it had already begun with
          the invitation to come to him, the King.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus replied with this parable:<JESUS>\u201CA man invited many to
        join him in a great feast.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>When the day for the feast arrived, the host instructed his
        servant to notify all the invited guests and tell them, \u2018Come, for everything
        is now ready for you!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>But one by one they all made excuses. One said, \u2018I can\u2019t
        come. I just bought some property and I have to go and look it over.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Another said, \u2018Please accept my regrets, for I just purchased
        five teams of oxen</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and I need to make sure
        they can pull the plow.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:19
        content: '  This implies he was a wealthy man who foolishly chose possessions
          over Christ.    '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>Another one said, \u2018I can\u2019t come because I just got
        married.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe servant reported back to the host and told him of
        all their excuses. The master became angry and said to his servant, \u2018Go
        at once throughout the city and invite anyone you find\u2014the poor, the
        blind, the disabled, the hurting, and the lonely. Invite them to my banquet.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen the servant returned to his master, he said, \u2018Sir,
        I have done what you asked, but there\u2019s still room for more.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSo the master told him, \u2018All right. Go out again,
        and this time bring them all back with you. Persuade the beggars on the streets,
        the outcasts, even the homeless. Insist that they come in and enjoy the feast
        so that my house will be full.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Cost of Following Jesus'
      title: The Cost of Following Jesus
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI say to you all, no one who receives an invitation
        to feast with me and makes excuses will ever enjoy my banquet.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'As massive crowds followed Jesus, he turned to them and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen you follow me as my disciple, you must put aside</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>your father, your mother, your wife, your sisters,
        your brothers; it will even seem as though you hate your own life. This is
        the price you\u2019ll pay to be considered one of my followers.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:26
        content: "  Or \u201Chate.\u201D This is an Aramaic and Hebraic metaphor
          for putting Jesus above every other relationship. The Aramaic word    has
          several meanings and can mean \u201Chate\u201D or \u201Cput aside.\u201D
          In this case, Jesus, the King of love is not saying to hate but to put
          aside every other relationship into second place. The meaning becomes quite
          clear in the Aramaic language.    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>Anyone who comes to me must be willing to share my cross and
        experience it as his own, or he cannot be considered to be my disciple.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>So don\u2019t follow me without considering what it will cost
        you. For who would construct a house</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>before
        first sitting down to estimate the cost to complete it?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:28
        content: "  Or \u201Ctower.\u201D    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>Otherwise he may lay the foundation and not be able to finish.
        The neighbors will ridicule him, saying,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>\u2018Look at him! He started to build but couldn\u2019t complete
        it!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHave you ever heard of a commander</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>who goes out to war without first sitting down with strategic planning
        to determine the strength of his army to win the war</JESUS>    <JESUS>against
        a stronger opponent?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:31
        content: "  Or \u201Cking.\u201D      The Greek text states, \u201CWith ten
          thousand he will be able to go up against twenty thousand.\u201D    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>If he knows he doesn\u2019t stand a chance of winning the
        war, the wise commander will send out delegates to ask for the terms of peace.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: <JESUS>Likewise, unless you surrender all to me, giving up all you
        possess, you cannot be one of my disciples.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSalt is good for seasoning. But if salt were to lose
        its flavor,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>how could it ever be restored?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:34
        content: "  Or \u201Cbecome foolish.\u201D Both Greek and Aramaic use a word
          that can mean \u201Cfoolish.\u201D If salt that has lost its flavor is
          foolish, then the salt that keeps its flavor is equal to wisdom. Rabbinical
          literature equates salt with wisdom. (Eduard Schweizer,  , Atlanta: John
          Knox Press, 1975.) After speaking of salt, Jesus, in  , goes on to refer
          to lighting a lamp. It was a common practice in the time of Jesus to put
          salt on the wick of a lamp to increase its brightness. The \u201Csalt\u201D
          of wisdom will make our light shine even brighter. (W. A. Elwell and P.W.
          Comfort,  , Tyndale reference library, Wheaton, Ill.: Tyndale House, 2001,
          797\u2013798.)    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>It will never be useful again, not even fit for the soil or
        the manure pile!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>If you have ears opened
        by the Spirit, then hear the meaning of what I have said</JESUS>  <JESUS>and
        apply it to yourselves</JESUS><JESUS>.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 14:35
        content: '  Followers of Jesus who are unwilling to pay the price of discipleship
          are like worthless salt, unable to affect anything or anyone.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Parable of the Lost Lamb'
      title: The Parable of the Lost Lamb
      number: 1
      content: 'Many dishonest tax collectors and other notorious sinners often gathered
        around to listen as Jesus taught the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This raised concerns among the Jewish religious leaders and experts
        of the law. Indignant, they grumbled and complained, saying, \u201CLook at
        how this man associates with all these notorious sinners and welcomes them
        all to come to him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In response, Jesus gave them this illustration: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThere once was a shepherd with a hundred lambs, but
        one of his lambs wandered away and was lost. So the shepherd left the ninety-nine
        lambs out in the open field and searched in the wilderness for that one lost
        lamb. He didn\u2019t stop until he finally found it. With exuberant joy,
        he raised it up, placed it on his shoulders,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and
        carried it back with cheerful delight!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: "15:4\u20135"
        content: "  What a wonderful picture this shepherd\u2019s joy gives us of
          our \u201CGood Shepherd.\u201D He doesn\u2019t beat the lost sheep for
          wandering away. He raises it up and carries it home!    "
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThere once was a shepherd with a hundred lambs, but
        one of his lambs wandered away and was lost. So the shepherd left the ninety-nine
        lambs out in the open field and searched in the wilderness for that one lost
        lamb. He didn\u2019t stop until he finally found it. With exuberant joy,
        he raised it up, placed it on his shoulders,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and
        carried it back with cheerful delight!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: "15:4\u20135"
        content: "  What a wonderful picture this shepherd\u2019s joy gives us of
          our \u201CGood Shepherd.\u201D He doesn\u2019t beat the lost sheep for
          wandering away. He raises it up and carries it home!    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>Returning home, he called all his friends and neighbors together
        and said, \u2018Let\u2019s have a party! Come and celebrate with me the return
        of my lost lamb. It wandered away, but I found it and brought it home.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Parable of the Lost Coin'
      title: The Parable of the Lost Coin
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CIn the same way, there will be a glorious
        celebration in heaven over the rescue of one lost sinner who repents, comes
        back home, and returns to the fold\u2014more so than for all the righteous
        people who never strayed away.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus gave them another parable: <JESUS>\u201CThere once was a woman
        who had ten</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>valuable silver coins. When she
        lost one of them, she swept her entire house, diligently searching every
        nook and cranny for that one lost coin.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:8
        content: "  The silver coin was a    (Aramaic). Although there are differing
          opinions as to its value, it could be equal in today\u2019s currency to
          more than twelve hundred US dollars. Notice the change of numbers in the
          three parables in this chapter: one out of a hundred for the sheep, one
          out of ten for the coins, and one out of two for the sons. This progressively
          shows the extraordinary value that Jesus places on every lost soul. Although
          the coin was lost, it never lost its value.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>When she finally found it, she gathered all her friends and
        neighbors for a celebration, telling them, \u2018Come and celebrate with
        me! I had lost my precious silver coin, but now I\u2019ve found it.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Loving Father'
      title: The Loving Father
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>That\u2019s the way God responds</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>every time one lost sinner repents and turns to him. He says to all
        his angels, \u2018Let\u2019s have a joyous celebration, for the one who was
        lost, I have found!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:10
        content: "  Jesus used the woman in this parable as a metaphor for God. A
          female image of God would incite anger from the Pharisees. In the next
          parable, God reveals himself as the extravagant Father who forgives his
          wayward son.      The silver coin had an image of Roman authority on it.
          We have been stamped with the image of God. Even when we are \u201Clost,\u201D
          that image is still present, needing only to be \u201Cfound\u201D and redeemed
          by grace.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201COnce there was a father with two sons.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>The younger son came to his father and said, \u2018Father,
        don\u2019t you think it\u2019s time to give me my share of your estate?\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>So the father went ahead and distributed between the
        two sons their inheritance.</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 15:12
        content: "  In the light of Middle Eastern culture, it was a great offense
          for a son to ask his father for his inheritance. It would be equivalent
          to saying, \u201CI wish you were already dead!\u201D      The Greek is
          literally \u201CHe gave them his life\u201D (Greek  ).    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: <JESUS>Shortly afterward, the younger son packed up all his belongings
        and traveled off to see the world. He journeyed to a far-off land where he
        soon wasted all he was given in a binge of extravagant and reckless living.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWith everything spent and nothing left, he grew hungry,
        because there was a severe famine in that land.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>So he begged a farmer in that country to hire him. The farmer
        hired him and sent him out to feed the pigs.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: <JESUS>The son was so famished, he was willing even to eat the slop
        given to the pigs,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>because no one would feed
        him a thing.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 15:16
        content: '  Tending pigs would be degrading to anyone, but especially to
          a Jew, who was forbidden to raise swine. See  ;  .    '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHumiliated, the son finally realized what he was doing,
        and he thought, \u2018There are many workers at my father\u2019s house who
        have all the food they want with plenty to spare. They lack nothing. Why
        am I here dying of hunger, feeding these pigs and eating their slop?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I want to go back home to my father\u2019s house, and I\u2019ll
        say to him, \u201CFather, I was wrong. I have sinned against you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>I\u2019ll never again be worthy to be called your son. Please,
        Father, just treat me like one of your employees.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSo the young son set off for home. From a long distance
        away, his father saw him coming,</JESUS>  <JESUS>dressed as a beggar,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and great compassion swelled up in his heart for his
        son who was returning home. The father raced out to meet him, swept him up
        in his arms, hugged him dearly, and kissed him over and over with tender
        love.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 15:20
        content: '  Implied in the context of the Greek text and stated more explicitly
          in the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThen the son said, \u2018Father, I was wrong. I have
        sinned against you. I could never deserve to be called your son. Just let
        me be\u2014\u2019</JESUS><JESUS>\u201CThe father interrupted and said,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u2018Son, you\u2019re home now!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 15:21
        content: '  This poetic description is made explicit from the cultural and
          spiritual implication of the text.    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CTurning to his servants, the father said, \u2018Quick,
        bring me the best robe, my very own robe, and I will place it on his shoulders.
        Bring the ring, the seal of sonship,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and
        I will put it on his finger. And bring out the best shoes</JESUS>    <JESUS>you
        can find for my son.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:22
        content: "  Culturally, this ring was an emblem of authority, a seal of sonship
          giving the son authority to transact business in his father\u2019s name.
          This was a picture of the seal of the Holy Spirit ().      Or \u201Cbring
          sandals for his feet.\u201D Slaves were barefoot.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>Let\u2019s</JESUS>  <JESUS>prepare a great feast</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and celebrate.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:23
        content: "  The Greek text is \u201Ckill the grain-fatted calf.\u201D This
          is a picture of feasting upon Christ, who was sacrificed for us.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>For my beloved son was once dead, but now he\u2019s alive!
        Once he was lost, but now he is found!\u2019 And everyone celebrated with
        overflowing joy.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CNow, the older son was out working in the field when
        his brother returned, and as he approached the house, he heard the music
        of celebration and dancing.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>He called over one of the servants and asked, \u2018What\u2019s
        going on?\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe servant replied, \u2018It\u2019s your younger brother.
        He\u2019s returned home and your father is throwing a party to celebrate
        his homecoming.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe older son became angry and refused to go in and
        celebrate. So his father came out and pleaded with him, \u2018Come and enjoy
        the feast with us!\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 15:28
        content: '  In the culture of that era, hospitality was of supreme importance.
          To refuse to go in to the feast, when it was his responsibility culturally
          to cohost the event with his father, was a humiliating rejection of the
          father.    '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe son said, \u2018Father, listen! How many years have
        I worked like a slave for you, performing every duty you\u2019ve asked as
        a faithful son?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And I\u2019ve never once
        disobeyed you. But you\u2019ve never thrown a party for me because of my
        faithfulness. Never once have you even given me a goat that I could feast
        on and celebrate with my friends as this son of yours is doing now.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:29
        content: '  While the younger brother pursued self-discovery, the older brother
          believed in moral conformity, earning favor from his father. Both needed
          the revelation of grace.    '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>Look at him! He comes back after wasting your wealth on prostitutes
        and reckless living, and here you are throwing a great feast to celebrate\u2014for
        him!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe father said, \u2018My son, you are always with me
        by my side. Everything I have is yours to enjoy.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>It\u2019s only right to rejoice and celebrate like this, because
        your brother was once dead and gone, but now he is alive and back with us
        again. He was lost, but now he is found!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 15:32
        content: '  Jesus spoke three parables unveiling and revealing how the Trinity
          desires to bring people back through the Son, by the Spirit, to the Father.
          The Son came as a shepherd, seeking and sacrificing to find the lost sinner.
          The Spirit seeks the lost sinner like the woman searched with the light
          of illumination for the lost coin until she found it. And the Father welcomes
          the returning sinner back to his house. It is the work of the Trinity to
          bring us back to God.  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Dishonest Manager'
      title: The Dishonest Manager
      number: 1
      content: "Jesus taught his disciples using this story:<JESUS>\u201COnce a very
        rich man hired a manager to run his business and oversee all his wealth.
        But soon a rumor spread that the manager was wasting his master\u2019s money.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>So the master called him in and said, \u2018Is it true that
        you are mismanaging my estate? You need to provide me with a complete audit
        of everything you oversee for me. I\u2019ve decided to dismiss you.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe manager thought, \u2018Now what am I going to do?
        I\u2019m finished here. I can\u2019t hide what I\u2019ve done,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and I\u2019m too proud to beg.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:3
        content: "  The manager\u2019s words include an ancient Aramaic figure of
          speech, \u201CI can\u2019t dig,\u201D which means it can\u2019t be buried
          or hidden.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>I have an idea that will secure my future. It will win me
        favor and secure friends who can take care of me and help me when I get fired!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSo the dishonest manager hatched his scheme. He went
        to everyone who owed his master money, one by one, and asked them, \u2018How
        much do you owe my master?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "<JESUS>One debtor owed twenty thousand dollars, so he said to him,
        \u2018Let me see your bill. Pay me now and we\u2019ll settle for twenty percent
        less.\u2019 The clever manager scratched out the original amount owed and
        reduced it by twenty percent. And to another who owed two hundred thousand
        dollars, he said, \u2018Pay me now and we\u2019ll reduce your bill by fifty
        percent.\u2019 And the clever manager scratched out the original amount owed
        and reduced it by half.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "<JESUS>One debtor owed twenty thousand dollars, so he said to him,
        \u2018Let me see your bill. Pay me now and we\u2019ll settle for twenty percent
        less.\u2019 The clever manager scratched out the original amount owed and
        reduced it by twenty percent. And to another who owed two hundred thousand
        dollars, he said, \u2018Pay me now and we\u2019ll reduce your bill by fifty
        percent.\u2019 And the clever manager scratched out the original amount owed
        and reduced it by half.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CEven though his master was defrauded, when he found
        out about the shrewd way this manager had feathered his own nest, he congratulated
        the clever scoundrel for what he\u2019d done to provide for his future.\u201D</JESUS>Jesus
        continued, <JESUS>\u201CRemember this: The sons of darkness interact more
        wisely than the sons of</JESUS> light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: <JESUS>Use the wealth of this world to demonstrate your friendship
        with God by winning friends and blessing others. Then, when it runs out,
        your generosity will provide you with an eternal reward.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 16:9
        content: "  Or \u201Cyou will be welcomed to the tents of eternity.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe one who faithfully manages the little he has been
        given will be promoted and trusted with greater responsibilities. But those
        who cheat with the little they have been given will not be considered trustworthy
        to receive more.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>If you have not handled the riches of this world with integrity,
        why should you be trusted with the eternal treasures of the spiritual world?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>And if you\u2019ve not proven yourself faithful with what
        belongs to another, why should you be given wealth of your own?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>It is impossible for a person to serve two masters at the
        same time. You will be forced to love one and reject the other. One master
        will be despised and the other will have your loyal devotion. Your choice
        between God and the wealth of this world</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>is
        no different. You must enthusiastically love one and definitively reject
        the other.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 16:13
        content: '  The word used here is  , which is money personified as a god
          and worshiped.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now, the Jewish religious leaders listening to Jesus were lovers
        of money. They laughed at what he said and mocked his teachings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "so Jesus addressed them directly. <JESUS>\u201CYou always want to
        look spiritual in the eyes of others, but you have forgotten the eyes of
        God, which see what is inside you. The very things that you approve of and
        applaud are the things God despises.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>The law of Moses and the revelation of the prophets have prepared
        you for the arrival of the kingdom announced by John. Since that time, the
        wonderful news of God\u2019s kingdom is being preached, and people\u2019s
        hearts burn with extreme passion to receive it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: <JESUS>Heaven and earth will disintegrate before even the smallest
        detail of the Law will fail or lose its power.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Rich Man and Lazarus'
      title: The Rich Man and Lazarus
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CIt is wrong for you to divorce</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>your wife so that you can marry another\u2014that is adultery. And
        when you take that one you lusted after as your wife, and contribute to the
        breakup of her marriage, you commit adultery again.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 16:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cdismiss,\u201D or \u201Csend away.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus continued. <JESUS>\u201CThere once was a very rich man who
        had the finest things imaginable,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>living
        every day enjoying his life of opulent luxury.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:19
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201CHe was dressed in a purple
          robe.\u201D This is a figure of speech that refers to the luxury that surrounded
          him. This was the kind of robe worn only by kings.    "
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: <JESUS>Outside the gate of his mansion</JESUS>  <JESUS>was a poor
        beggar named Lazarus.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>He lay there every
        day, covered with boils, and all the neighborhood dogs would come and lick
        his open sores. The only food he had to eat was the garbage that the rich
        man threw away.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: "16:20\u201321"
        content: "    is a form of the name Eleazar and means \u201CGod helps.\u201D    "
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: <JESUS>Outside the gate of his mansion</JESUS>  <JESUS>was a poor
        beggar named Lazarus.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>He lay there every
        day, covered with boils, and all the neighborhood dogs would come and lick
        his open sores. The only food he had to eat was the garbage that the rich
        man threw away.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: "16:20\u201321"
        content: "    is a form of the name Eleazar and means \u201CGod helps.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201COne day poor Lazarus died, and the angels of God came
        and escorted his spirit into paradise.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 16:22
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201CAbraham\u2019s bosom,\u201D
          which is a metaphor for paradise.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe day came that the rich man also died. In hell he
        looked up from his torment and saw Abraham in the distance, and Lazarus was
        standing beside him in the glory.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>The rich man shouted, \u2018Father Abraham! Father Abraham!
        Have mercy on me. Send Lazarus to dip his finger in water and come to cool
        my tongue, for I am in agony in these flames of fire!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBut Abraham responded, \u2018My friend, don\u2019t you
        remember? While you were alive, you had all you desired. You surrounded yourself
        in luxury, while Lazarus had nothing. Now Lazarus dwells in the comforts
        of paradise and you are in agony.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>Besides, between us is a huge chasm that cannot be bridged,
        nor can anyone cross from one realm to the other, even if he wanted.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe rich man continued, \u2018Then let me ask you, Father
        Abraham, please send Lazarus to my relatives.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>Tell him to witness to my five brothers and warn them not
        to end up where I am in this place of torment.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAbraham replied, \u2018They\u2019ve already had plenty
        of warning. They have the teachings of Moses and the</JESUS>  <JESUS>revelation
        of the</JESUS>  <JESUS>prophets; let them hear them.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>\u201C&nbsp;\u2018What if they\u2019re not listening?\u2019
        the rich man added. \u2018If someone from the dead were to go and warn them,
        they would surely repent.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAbraham said to him, \u2018If they wouldn\u2019t listen
        to Moses and the prophets, neither would they be convinced if someone</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>were raised from the dead!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 16:31
        content: "  Translated from the Aramaic. Jesus is that \u201Csomeone\u201D
          who rose from the grave, yet many still will not listen and believe.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Faith and Forgiveness'
      title: Faith and Forgiveness
      number: 1
      content: "One day Jesus taught his disciples: <JESUS>\u201CBetrayals</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>are inevitable, but great devastation will come to
        the one guilty of betraying others.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 17:1
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Other Greek texts use the words
          \u201Ctemptation\u201D or \u201Cto stumble.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>It would be better for him to have a heavy boulder tied around
        his neck and be hurled into the deepest sea than to face the punishment of
        betraying one of my dear ones! So be alert to your brother\u2019s condition,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>and if you see him going the wrong direction, cry out and
        correct him. If there is true repentance on his part, forgive him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>No matter how many times in one day your brother sins against
        you</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and says, \u2018I\u2019m sorry; I am
        changing; forgive me,\u2019 you need to forgive him each and every time.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:4
        content: "  The Greek text states explicitly \u201Cseven times.\u201D But
          this is used as a metaphor for unlimited forgiveness.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Upon hearing this, the apostles said to Jesus, \u201CLord, you must
        increase [[COMMENT(0)]] our measure of faith!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 17:5
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201Cadd faith to us.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CIf you have even the smallest measure
        of faith, it would be powerful enough to say to this large</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>tree, \u2018My faith will pull you up by the roots and throw you into
        the sea,\u2019</JESUS>  <JESUS>and it will respond to your faith</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>and obey you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 17:6
        content: "  The Greek text is \u201Cmulberry\u201D or \u201Csycamore tree,\u201D
          which is known to grow to about thirty-five feet high.      The apostles
          had faith; they simply needed to use it.    "
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CAfter a servant has finished his work
        in the field or with the livestock, he doesn\u2019t immediately sit down
        to relax and eat. No, a true servant prepares the food for his master and
        makes sure his master is served his meal before he sits down to eat his own.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CAfter a servant has finished his work
        in the field or with the livestock, he doesn\u2019t immediately sit down
        to relax and eat. No, a true servant prepares the food for his master and
        makes sure his master is served his meal before he sits down to eat his own.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>Does the servant expect to be thanked for doing what is required
        of him?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jesus Heals Ten Lepers'
      title: Jesus Heals Ten Lepers
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>So learn this lesson: After doing all that is commanded of
        you, simply say, \u2018We are mere servants, undeserving of special praise,
        for we are just doing what is expected of us and fulfilling our duties.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On his way to Jerusalem Jesus passed through the border region between
        Samaria and Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'As he entered one village, ten men approached him, but they kept
        their distance, for they were lepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They shouted to him, \u201CMighty Lord, our wonderful Master! [[COMMENT(0)]]
        Won\u2019t you have mercy on us and heal us?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 17:13
        content: "  The Greek word used here for \u201CMaster\u201D is not the usual
          word used for \u201CTeacher\u201D or \u201CMaster.\u201D It denotes one
          with supernatural authority and power.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Jesus stopped to look at them, he spoke these words: <JESUS>\u201CGo
        to be examined by the Jewish priests.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]They set
        off, and they were healed while walking along the way. "
      comments:
      - number: 17:14
        content: '  This was what was required. See  ;  . What a step of faith for
          these lepers as they stepped out on only the word Jesus spoke to them.
          They were to go to the priest, who would confirm their healing and declare
          them ceremonially clean and approved to go into the temple to worship God.    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'One of them, a Samaritan, [[COMMENT(0)]] when he discovered that
        he was completely healed, turned back to find Jesus, shouting out joyous
        praises and glorifying God. '
      comments:
      - number: 17:15
        content: "  For a Samaritan man to give thanks to a Jewish man was indeed
          peculiar. Since he likely had no \u201Cpriest,\u201D he turned to the only
          one he knew to be a priest for him, Jesus Christ.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When he found Jesus, he fell down at his feet and thanked him over
        and over, saying to him, \u201CYou are the Messiah.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 17:16
        content: '  From the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSo where are the other nine?\u201D</JESUS> Jesus asked.
        <JESUS>\u201CWeren\u2019t there ten who were healed?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>They all refused to return to give thanks and give glory to
        God except you, a foreigner from Samaria?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: "19: God\u2019s Kingdom Realm within You"
      title: "God\u2019s Kingdom Realm within You"
      number: 19
      content: "Then Jesus said to the healed man lying at his feet, <JESUS>\u201CArise
        and go. It was your faith that brought you salvation and made you whole.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jesus was once asked by the Jewish religious leaders, \u201CWhen
        will God\u2019s kingdom come?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CGod\u2019s
        kingdom does not come simply</JESUS>  <JESUS>by obeying principles</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>or waiting for signs.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 17:20
        content: "  Or \u201CWhen will God\u2019s kingdom be established?\u201D     
          Implied in the Aramaic text where it states, \u201Cobservances\u201D (of
          the law). The same word is found in    referring to \u201Cobservances\u201D
          of keeping the law.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>The kingdom is not discovered in one place or another, for
        God\u2019s kingdom realm is already expanding within some of you.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 17:21
        content: "  Translated from the Aramaic text. The implication is that God\u2019s
          kingdom realm is a person, Jesus Christ. The reality of God\u2019s kingdom
          appears when Jesus lives within us by faith.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Later, Jesus addressed this again with his apostles, saying, <JESUS>\u201CThe
        time is coming when a great passion will be awakened within you to see me
        again. Yes, you will long to see the beginning of the days of the Son of
        Man, but you won\u2019t be able to find me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>You will hear reports from some who will say, \u2018Look,
        he has returned,\u2019 \u2018He\u2019s over here,\u2019 or, \u2018He\u2019s
        over there!\u2019 Don\u2019t believe it or run after them,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for
        their claims will be false.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: <JESUS>The day of the Son of Man will burst forth with the brightness
        of a lightning strike that shines from one end of the sky to the other, illuminating
        the earth.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBut before this takes place, the Son of Man must pass
        through great suffering and rejection from this generation.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>The same things that happened in the days of Noah will take
        place in the days of the Son of Man.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: <JESUS>They were eating, they were drinking, they were marrying, and
        they were given in marriage until the day Noah boarded the ark and the devastating
        flood came and swept them all away.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '28-30: '
      title: 
      number: 28-30
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe days of the Son of Man can also be compared to the
        days of Lot. The people of that time lived their lives as normal. They got
        married, raised families, built homes and businesses, yet they were totally
        unaware of what was coming until the day Lot departed from Sodom. The sky
        opened up and rained fire and burning sulfur upon them, destroying everyone
        and everything they had built. So it will be on the day of the unveiling
        of the Son of Man.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '28-30: '
      title: 
      number: 28-30
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe days of the Son of Man can also be compared to the
        days of Lot. The people of that time lived their lives as normal. They got
        married, raised families, built homes and businesses, yet they were totally
        unaware of what was coming until the day Lot departed from Sodom. The sky
        opened up and rained fire and burning sulfur upon them, destroying everyone
        and everything they had built. So it will be on the day of the unveiling
        of the Son of Man.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '28-30: '
      title: 
      number: 28-30
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe days of the Son of Man can also be compared to the
        days of Lot. The people of that time lived their lives as normal. They got
        married, raised families, built homes and businesses, yet they were totally
        unaware of what was coming until the day Lot departed from Sodom. The sky
        opened up and rained fire and burning sulfur upon them, destroying everyone
        and everything they had built. So it will be on the day of the unveiling
        of the Son of Man.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>\u201COn that day, if one is outside,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>he won\u2019t even have time to go back into the house to gather his
        belongings. And those toiling in their fields won\u2019t have time to run
        back home.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 17:31
        content: "  The Greek text is literally \u201Con the roof.\u201D    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t forget the example of Lot\u2019s wife and what
        happened to her when she turned back.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 17:32
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>All who are obsessed with being secure in life will lose it
        all\u2014including their lives. But those who let go of their lives and surrender
        them to me will discover true life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>For in that night there will be two lying in their bed; one
        will be suddenly swept away while the other will be left</JESUS>  <JESUS>alive</JESUS><JESUS>.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35-36: '
      title: 
      number: 35-36
      content: "<JESUS>There will be two women working together at household duties;
        one will be suddenly swept away while the other will be left</JESUS>  <JESUS>alive</JESUS><JESUS>.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "17:35\u201336"
        content: "  This Greek word can also refer to being \u201Cforgiven of sin.\u201D
          Some later Greek texts add, \u201CTwo men will be in the field; one will
          be taken and the other will be left. Those who are swept away are taken
          to judgment; those who are left behind remain to enter into the kingdom
          glory.\u201D    "
    - name: '35-36: '
      title: 
      number: 35-36
      content: "<JESUS>There will be two women working together at household duties;
        one will be suddenly swept away while the other will be left</JESUS>  <JESUS>alive</JESUS><JESUS>.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: "17:35\u201336"
        content: "  This Greek word can also refer to being \u201Cforgiven of sin.\u201D
          Some later Greek texts add, \u201CTwo men will be in the field; one will
          be taken and the other will be left. Those who are swept away are taken
          to judgment; those who are left behind remain to enter into the kingdom
          glory.\u201D    "
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "His apostles asked, \u201CLord, where will this judgment happen?\u201DJesus
        responded, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>It will be obvious</JESUS><JESUS>,
        for wherever there are those spiritually dead,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>there
        you will find the eagles</JESUS>    <JESUS>circling.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:37
        content: "  The Greek word used here is literally \u201Ccorpse\u201D and
          can be a metaphor for those who are spiritually dead.      The Greek word
          used here can be translated \u201Ceagles\u201D or \u201Cvultures.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Gives a Parable about Prayer'
      title: Jesus Gives a Parable about Prayer
      number: 1
      content: 'One day Jesus taught the apostles to keep praying and never stop
        or lose hope. He shared with them this illustration:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CIn a certain town there was a judge, a thick-skinned
        and godless man who had no fear of others\u2019 opinions.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>And in the same town there was a poor widow who kept pleading
        with the judge, \u2018Grant me justice and protect me from my oppressor!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHe ignored her pleas for quite some time, but she kept
        asking. Eventually he said to himself, \u2018This widow keeps annoying me,
        demanding her rights, and I\u2019m tired of listening to her. Even though
        I\u2019m not a religious man, and I don\u2019t care about the opinions of
        others, I\u2019ll get her off my back by answering her claims for justice
        and I\u2019ll rule in her favor. Then she\u2019ll leave me alone.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '4-5: '
      title: 
      number: 4-5
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHe ignored her pleas for quite some time, but she kept
        asking. Eventually he said to himself, \u2018This widow keeps annoying me,
        demanding her rights, and I\u2019m tired of listening to her. Even though
        I\u2019m not a religious man, and I don\u2019t care about the opinions of
        others, I\u2019ll get her off my back by answering her claims for justice
        and I\u2019ll rule in her favor. Then she\u2019ll leave me alone.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CDid you hear what the godless judge
        said\u2014that he would answer her persistent request?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t you know that God, the true judge, will grant justice
        to all his chosen ones who cry out to him night and day? He will pour out
        his Spirit upon them.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>He will not delay to
        answer you and give you what you ask for.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 18:7
        content: "  Translated from the Aramaic text. The Greek text has an unusual
          verb that means \u201Cever tapping,\u201D signifying one who keeps knocking
          on the door of heaven until he receives what he came for.    "
    - name: '8: Humility in Prayer'
      title: Humility in Prayer
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>God will give swift justice to those who don\u2019t give up.
        So be ever praying, ever expecting, in the same way as the widow. Even so,
        when the Son of Man comes back, will he find this kind of undying faith on
        earth?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Jesus taught this parable to those who were convinced they were morally
        upright and to those who trusted in their own virtue yet looked down on others
        with disgust:'
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CTwo men who went into the temple to pray. One was a
        proud religious leader, the other a despised tax collector.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "<JESUS>The religious leader stood apart from the others and prayed,
        \u2018How I thank you, O&nbsp;God, that I\u2019m not wicked like everyone
        else. They\u2019re cheaters, swindlers, and crooks\u2014like that tax collector
        over there. God, you know that I never cheat or commit adultery; I fast from
        food twice a week and I give you a tenth of all I earn.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '11-12: '
      title: 
      number: 11-12
      content: "<JESUS>The religious leader stood apart from the others and prayed,
        \u2018How I thank you, O&nbsp;God, that I\u2019m not wicked like everyone
        else. They\u2019re cheaters, swindlers, and crooks\u2014like that tax collector
        over there. God, you know that I never cheat or commit adultery; I fast from
        food twice a week and I give you a tenth of all I earn.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe tax collector stood alone in a corner,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>away from the Holy Place</JESUS><JESUS>, and covered his face in his
        hands, feeling that he was unworthy even to look up to God. Beating his breast,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>he sobbed with brokenness and tears saying, \u2018God,
        please, in your mercy</JESUS>  <JESUS>and because of the blood sacrifice,
        forgive me,</JESUS>    <JESUS>for I am nothing but the most miserable of
        all sinners!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 18:13
        content: "  The Greek verb  , means \u201Cto strike,\u201D or \u201Cto strike
          dead.\u201D It is a violent term also used of the scourging of Jesus.     
          The Greek text uses a word that implies he was saying to God, \u201CLook
          at me as you look at the blood-sprinkled mercy seat.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: Jesus Blesses Children'
      title: Jesus Blesses Children
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhich one of them left for home that day reconciled
        to God? The humble tax collector, not the religious leader! For everyone
        who praises himself will one day be publicly humiliated, and everyone who
        humbles himself will one day be publicly honored and lifted up.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The people brought their babies and small children [[COMMENT(0)]]
        to Jesus so that he might lay his hands on them to bless them. When the disciples
        saw this, they scolded the parents and told them to stop troubling the Master. '
      comments:
      - number: 18:15
        content: '  There is a hint in the Greek text that these children may have
          been sick. Jesus loves and heals children.    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Seeing what was happening, Jesus called for the parents, the children,
        and his disciples to come and listen to him. Then he told them, <JESUS>\u201CNever
        hinder a child from coming to me but let them all come, for God\u2019s kingdom
        belongs to them as much as it does to anyone else.</JESUS>  <JESUS>These
        children demonstrate to you what faith is all about.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jesus Speaks with a Young, Wealthy Official'
      title: Jesus Speaks with a Young, Wealthy Official
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>Learn this well: unless you receive the revelation of the
        kingdom the same way a little child receives it, you will never be able to
        enter in.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "One day a wealthy Jewish nobleman of high standing posed this question
        to Jesus: \u201CWonderful Teacher, what must I do to receive eternal life?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CWhy would you call me wonderful when
        there is only one who is wonderful\u2014and that is God alone?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 18:19
        content: "  Jesus is implying that if we call him \u201Cwonderful,\u201D
          we are calling him \u201CGod.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>You already know what is right and what the commandments teach:
        \u2018Do not commit adultery, do not murder, do not steal, do not lie, and
        honor your father and your mother.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The wealthy leader replied, \u201CThese are the very things I\u2019ve
        been doing for as long as I can remember.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAh,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201Cthere\u2019s
        still one thing you\u2019re missing in your life.\u201D</JESUS>\u201CWhat
        is that?\u201D asked the man.<JESUS>\u201CYou must go and sell everything
        you own and give all the proceeds to the poor so you will have eternal treasures.
        Then come and follow me.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:22
        content: "  Jesus was not teaching that salvation can be earned by giving
          away our possessions to the poor. Jesus was showing the young, wealthy
          man that he couldn\u2019t truly be a disciple until there was no competition
          in his heart to following Jesus.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: These words devastated the rich leader, for he was extremely wealthy.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Jesus saw his disappointment, and looking right at him said, <JESUS>\u201CIt
        is next to impossible for those who have everything to enter into God\u2019s
        kingdom.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>Nothing could be harder! You could compare it to trying to
        stuff a rope through the eye of a needle.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:25
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek is \u201Cto stuff a
          camel through the eye of a needle.\u201D The Aramaic word for \u201Crope\u201D
          and for \u201Ccamel\u201D is the homonym  . This could be an instance of
          the Aramaic text being misread by the Greek translators as \u201Ccamel\u201D
          instead of \u201Crope.\u201D Regardless, Jesus used a metaphor for something
          impossible. It would be like saying, \u201CIt\u2019s as hard as making
          pigs fly!\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Those who heard this said, \u201CThen who can be saved?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CWhat appears humanly impossible is
        more than possible with God. For God can do what man cannot.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Peter said, \u201CMaster, see how we\u2019ve left all that we have,
        our houses and our careers, to follow you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29-30: Jesus Prophesies His Death and Resurrection'
      title: Jesus Prophesies His Death and Resurrection
      number: 29-30
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CListen to my words: anyone who leaves
        his home behind and chooses God\u2019s kingdom over wife, children, parents,
        and family, it will come back to him many more times in this lifetime.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And in the age to come, he will inherit even more
        than that\u2014he will inherit eternal life!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "18:29\u201330"
        content: "  Mark\u2019s Gospel adds, \u201Cand with persecutions.\u201D See 
          .    "
    - name: '29-30: Jesus Prophesies His Death and Resurrection'
      title: Jesus Prophesies His Death and Resurrection
      number: 29-30
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CListen to my words: anyone who leaves
        his home behind and chooses God\u2019s kingdom over wife, children, parents,
        and family, it will come back to him many more times in this lifetime.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And in the age to come, he will inherit even more
        than that\u2014he will inherit eternal life!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "18:29\u201330"
        content: "  Mark\u2019s Gospel adds, \u201Cand with persecutions.\u201D See 
          .    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus took the Twelve aside and told them in private, <JESUS>\u201CWe
        are going to Jerusalem so that everything prophesied about the Son of Man
        will be fulfilled.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>They will betray him and hand him over to the people, and
        they will mock him, insult him, and spit in his face.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>And after they have abused</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and
        flogged the Son of Man, they will kill him. But in three days he will rise
        again.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 18:33
        content: "  The word translated \u201Cabused\u201D is powerful. It occurs
          in the Greek text in v.    but in the Aramaic text in v.  .    "
    - name: '34: Jesus Heals a Blind Beggar'
      title: Jesus Heals a Blind Beggar
      number: 34
      content: The disciples had no clue what he was saying, for his words were a
        mystery that was hidden from them.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'As Jesus and his followers arrived at Jericho, a blind beggar was
        sitting by the roadside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "When he heard the crowd approaching, he asked, \u201CWhat\u2019s
        all this commotion about?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CIt\u2019s Jesus!\u201D they said. \u201CJesus the Nazarene
        is passing by.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "The blind beggar shouted, \u201CJesus, Son of David, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        have pity and show me mercy!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 18:38
        content: '  The term    was used for the Messiah. The blind man believed
          Jesus was the Messiah.    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Those in the front of the crowd scolded him and warned him to be
        quiet, but the blind beggar screamed out even louder, \u201CJesus, Son of
        David, show me mercy!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Suddenly Jesus stopped and directed those nearby, <JESUS>\u201CBring
        the man over to me.\u201D</JESUS> When they brought him before Jesus, he
        asked the man, "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhat do you want me to do for you?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CMaster,\u201D
        he said, \u201Cplease, I want to see.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CNow you will see. Receive your sight this
        moment, for your faith in me has given you sight and new life.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:42
        content: '  Translated from the Aramaic. The Greek word signifies both healing
          and salvation.  '
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Instantly he could see again. His eyes popped open, and he saw Jesus
        standing in front of him! He shouted loud praises to God and he followed
        Jesus. And when the crowd saw what happened, they too erupted with shouts
        of praise to God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus and Zacchaeus'
      title: Jesus and Zacchaeus
      number: 1
      content: 'On his way to Jerusalem, Jesus had to pass through Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There lived a very wealthy man named Zacchaeus, [[COMMENT(0)]] who
        supervised all the tax collectors. '
      comments:
      - number: 19:2
        content: "  The name Zacchaeus means \u201Cpure.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He was very eager to see Jesus and kept trying to get a look at him
        through the massive crowd. Since Zacchaeus was a short man and couldn\u2019t
        see over the heads of the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: he ran on ahead of everyone and climbed up a blossoming fig tree [[COMMENT(0)]]
        to get a glimpse of Jesus as he passed by.
      comments:
      - number: 19:4
        content: "  This was a sturdy sycamore-fig tree that was known to reach over
          forty feet high. The Aramaic text calls it a \u201Ctree in bloom.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When Jesus got to that place, he looked up into the tree and said,
        <JESUS>\u201CZacchaeus, hurry on down, for I must</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>stay at your house today!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 19:5
        content: "  Although they had never met, Jesus knew Zacchaeus\u2019 name.
          This was a \u201Cword of revelation knowledge ().\u201D The Aramaic text
          states, \u201CIt is my duty to stay at your house.\u201D It is likely that
          Jesus spent the night in Zacchaeus\u2019 home.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So he scurried down the tree and found himself face-to-face with Jesus.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As Jesus left to go with Zacchaeus, many in the crowd complained,
        \u201CLook at this! Of all the people to have dinner [[COMMENT(0)]] with,
        he\u2019s going to eat in the house of a crook.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 19:7
        content: "  The Aramaic states \u201Cdinner after the fast.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Zacchaeus was amazed over his gracious visit to his home and joyously
        welcomed Jesus. [[COMMENT(0)]] Zacchaeus stood in front of the Lord and said,
        \u201CHalf of all that I own I will give to the poor. And Lord, if I have
        cheated anyone, I promise to pay them back four times as much as I stole.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 19:8
        content: '  This is supplied from v.  , stated here for the sake of the narrative.     
          Jewish laws for restitution required repayment of a multiple of what was
          stolen. See  , where King David decrees a fourfold restitution.    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CYour repentance shows that today
        life</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>has come to you and your household,
        and that you are a true son of Abraham.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 19:9
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek text is \u201Csalvation.\u201D
          Notice that Jesus describes himself as both \u201Clife\u201D and \u201CSon
          of Man.\u201D He is both divine and human.    "
    - name: '10: The Parable of a Prince and His Servants'
      title: The Parable of a Prince and His Servants
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>The Son of Man has come to seek out and to give life to those
        who are lost.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:10
        content: "  This is a quotation taken from  . Notice that Jesus describes
          himself as both \u201Clife\u201D and \u201CSon of Man.\u201D He is both
          divine and human.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "At this time Jesus was getting close to entering Jerusalem. The crowds
        that followed him were convinced that God\u2019s kingdom would fully manifest
        when Jesus established it in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So he told them this story to change their perspective:<JESUS>\u201COnce
        a wealthy prince left his province to travel to a distant land, where he
        would be crowned king and then return.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>Before he departed he summoned his ten servants together and
        charged them, \u2018I am entrusting each of you with fifty thousand dollars</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to invest while I am away. Trade with it and put the
        money to work until I return.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 19:13
        content: "  Literally \u201Cten minas.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSome of his countrymen despised the prince and sent
        a delegation after him to declare before the royals, \u2018We refuse to let
        this man rule over us! He will not be our king!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CNevertheless, he was crowned king and returned to his
        land. Then he summoned his ten servants to see how much each one had earned
        and what their profits came to.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe first one came forward and said, \u2018Master, I
        took what you gave me and invested it, and it multiplied ten times.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>\u201C&nbsp;\u2018Splendid! You have done well, my excellent
        servant. Because you have shown that I can trust you in this small matter,
        I now grant you authority to rule over ten cities.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe second came and said, \u2018Master, what you left
        with me has multiplied five times.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHis master said, \u2018I also grant you authority in
        my kingdom over five cities.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnother came before the king and said, \u2018Master,
        here is the money you entrusted to me. I hid it for safekeeping.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>You see, I live in fear of you, for everyone knows you are
        a strict master and impossible to please. You push us for a high return on
        all that you own, and you always want to gain from someone else\u2019s efforts.\u2019</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:21
        content: "  The text is literally \u201CYou pick up what you didn\u2019t
          lay down and reap where you didn\u2019t sow.\u201D This statement is obviously
          not true. The opposite can be found in how the master shared his kingdom
          with the other more faithful servants. Today, many likewise have a misconception
          of the true heart of our Master. Our Master makes servants into rulers.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe king said, \u2018You wicked servant! I will judge
        you using your own words. If what you said about me is true, that I am a
        harsh man, pushing you for a high return and wanting gain from others\u2019
        efforts,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>why didn\u2019t you at least put my money in the bank</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to earn some interest on it?\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 19:23
        content: "  The text is literally \u201Cupon a table,\u201D a metaphor for
          where banking transactions took place.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe king said to his other servants, \u2018Take the
        money he has and give it to the faithful servant who multiplied my money
        ten times over.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201C&nbsp;\u2018But master,\u2019 the other servants objected,
        \u2018why give it to him? He already has so much!\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>\u201C&nbsp;\u2018Yes,\u2019 replied the king. \u2018But to
        all who have been faithful, I will give even more to them. And for the ones
        who have nothing, even the little they seem to have I will take from them.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Jesus\u2019 Final Approach to Jerusalem"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Final Approach to Jerusalem"
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>Now, bring all those rebellious enemies of mine who rejected
        me as their king\u2014bring them here before me and execute them!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'After saying all of this, Jesus headed straight for Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When he arrived at the stables of Annia [[COMMENT(0)]] near the Mount
        of Olives,  he sent two of his disciples ahead, saying, '
      comments:
      - number: 19:29
        content: "  The Greek text includes two small villages, Bethphage and Bethany.
          The meaning of the names combined means \u201Cthe stables of Annia.\u201D
          This is how it is translated in the Aramaic.      The Mount of Olives is
          a large hill less than two miles from Jerusalem and about one hundred feet
          higher.    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen you enter the next village,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>you will find tethered there a donkey\u2019s young colt that has never
        been ridden. Untie it and bring it to me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 19:30
        content: "  Literally \u201Cacross the valley.\u201D    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>And if anyone stops you and asks, \u2018What are you doing?\u2019
        just tell them this: \u2018It is needed for the Lord.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:31
        content: '  The Lord Jesus created all things and therefore owns it all.    '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The two disciples entered the village and found the colt exactly
        like Jesus had said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "While they were untying it, the owners confronted them and asked,
        \u201CWhat are you doing?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The disciples replied, \u201CWe need this donkey for the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35-36: '
      title: 
      number: 35-36
      content: 'After they brought the colt to Jesus, they placed their prayer shawls
        on its back, and Jesus rode it as he descended the Mount of Olives toward
        Jerusalem. [[COMMENT(0)]] As he rode toward the city, people spontaneously
        threw their prayer shawls like a carpet on the path in front of him. '
      comments:
      - number: "19:35\u201336"
        content: '  See  .      This was done to signify Jesus was King. See  . This
          is an obvious reference to the coming of the promised Messiah.    '
    - name: '35-36: '
      title: 
      number: 35-36
      content: 'After they brought the colt to Jesus, they placed their prayer shawls
        on its back, and Jesus rode it as he descended the Mount of Olives toward
        Jerusalem. [[COMMENT(0)]] As he rode toward the city, people spontaneously
        threw their prayer shawls like a carpet on the path in front of him. '
      comments:
      - number: "19:35\u201336"
        content: '  See  .      This was done to signify Jesus was King. See  . This
          is an obvious reference to the coming of the promised Messiah.    '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'As soon as he got to the bottom of the Mount of Olives, the crowd
        of his followers shouted with a loud outburst of ecstatic joy over all the
        mighty wonders of power they had witnessed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "They shouted over and over, \u201CHighest praises to God for the
        one who comes as King in the name of the Lord! Heaven\u2019s peace and glory
        from the highest realm now comes to us!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:38
        content: '  This is a quotation of  .    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Some Jewish religious leaders who stood off from the procession said
        to Jesus, \u201CTeacher, order your followers at once to stop saying these
        things!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: Jesus Weeps over Jerusalem'
      title: Jesus Weeps over Jerusalem
      number: 40
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CListen to me. If my followers were
        silenced, the very stones would break forth with praises!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'When Jesus caught sight of the city, he burst into tears with uncontrollable
        weeping over Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "saying, <JESUS>\u201CIf only you could recognize that this day peace
        is within your reach! But you cannot see it.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '<JESUS>For the day is soon coming when your enemies will surround
        you, hem you in on every side, and lay siege to you.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 19:43
        content: "  Translated from the Aramaic. The Greek text states, \u201CThey
          will throw up ramparts.\u201D See  ;  ;  . Jesus was the only one weeping
          while everyone else was rejoicing.    "
    - name: '44: Jesus Cleanses the Temple Courts'
      title: Jesus Cleanses the Temple Courts
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>They will crush you to pieces, and your children too! And
        they will leave your city totally destroyed. Since you would not recognize
        God\u2019s day of visitation, you will see your day of devastation!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jesus entered the temple area and forcibly threw out all the merchants
        from their stalls. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "He rebuked them, saying, <JESUS>\u201CThe Scriptures declare, \u2018My
        Father\u2019s house is to be filled with prayer\u2014a house of prayer,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>not a cave of bandits!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 19:46
        content: '  See  ;  .  '
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'From then on Jesus continued teaching in the temple area, but the
        high priests, the experts of the law, and the prominent men of the city kept
        trying to find a strategy to accuse Jesus, for they wanted him dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: They could find no reason to accuse him, for he was a hero to the
        people and the crowds were awestruck by every word he spoke.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Day of Controversy'
      title: A Day of Controversy
      number: 1
      content: 'One day Jesus was teaching in the temple courts and sharing with
        the people the wonderful news of salvation. [[COMMENT(0)]] The high priest,
        the experts of the law, and the prominent men of the city confronted Jesus
        and asked him, '
      comments:
      - number: 20:1
        content: '  Translated from the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWe want to know right now by what authority are you teaching
        here in the temple? And who gave you the authority to teach these things?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CFirst, let me ask you a question and
        you tell me right now.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>Did John baptize because he had a commission from heaven or
        merely from men?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "His interrogators pulled themselves aside to consider how to respond
        to Jesus. \u201CWhat should we say? If we say that John\u2019s mandate was
        from heaven, he will ask us, \u2018Then why didn\u2019t you believe him and
        be baptized?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But if we say, \u2018John\u2019s mandate was merely from men,\u2019
        then all the people around him will stone us, for they believe John was a
        prophet of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So unable to devise an answer they said to Jesus, \u201CWe cannot
        tell where John\u2019s authority came from.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Story of the Vine Growers'
      title: The Story of the Vine Growers
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CThen neither will I tell you by what authority
        I do these things.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus taught the people using this story:<JESUS>\u201CA man once
        planted a vineyard, then leased it out to tenants. Then he left to go abroad
        and was away for a long time.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>At harvest time, the owner sent one of his servants to the
        tenants to collect the landowner\u2019s share of the harvest, but the tenants
        sent him away, beaten and empty-handed.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>So the owner dispatched another one of his servants to collect
        his portion, but the tenants treated him the same way. They cursed him, beat
        him, and sent him away empty-handed.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>Then the owner sent a third servant, but they brutalized him
        also with the same treatment.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>Finally the owner of the vineyard said to his son, \u2018Perhaps
        if I send you, my own cherished son, they will be ashamed of what they\u2019ve
        done.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:13
        content: '  Translated from the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBut when the tenants saw the son coming, they schemed
        among themselves. \u2018This is the heir of the vineyard! If we kill him,
        the inheritance will be ours.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>So they threw the son off the property and killed him.</JESUS><JESUS>\u201CI
        ask you, what do you think the owner of the vineyard will do to his son\u2019s
        murderers?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>He will come back and destroy them and give his vineyard to
        another.\u201D</JESUS>When the people heard this story, they all agreed,
        \u201CThis should never happen!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus looked straight at the people and their leaders and said, <JESUS>\u201CWhat
        do you think this verse means? \u2018The worthless, rejected stone has become
        the cornerstone, the most important stone of all.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 20:17
        content: '  See  ;  ;  .    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>Everyone who falls</JESUS>  <JESUS>in humility</JESUS>  <JESUS>upon
        that stone will be broken. But if that stone falls on you, it will grind
        you to pieces!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Paying Taxes'
      title: Paying Taxes
      number: 19
      content: When the high priests and experts of the law realized that this story
        was about them, they wanted to have Jesus arrested that very moment, but
        they were afraid of all the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Later, they sent spies who pretended to be honest seekers, but who
        wanted an opportunity to entangle Jesus by his words. Their plan was to catch
        him saying something against the government, so they could hand him over
        to the jurisdiction of the Roman authorities who would execute him for sedition.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "At the right time they asked him this question: \u201CTeacher, we
        know that all you say is straightforward and what you teach us is right.
        You give us the true ways of God. You\u2019re one who shows no favoritism
        to anyone\u2019s status. So we ask you\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "is it proper or not to pay taxes to a corrupt government?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:22
        content: "  The Greek text states, \u201Cto the emperor.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus saw right through their cunning ploy and said, <JESUS>\u201CWhy
        are you testing me?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 20:23
        content: '  Although not found in most Greek manuscripts, it is included
          in the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Show me one of the Roman coins. Whose head is on the coin?
        Whose title is stamped on it?\u201D</JESUS>They answered, \u201CWhy, it\u2019s
        Caesar\u2019s.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CPrecisely. The coin</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>bears the image of the Emperor Caesar, and you should give back to
        Caesar all that belongs to him. But you bear the image of God. So give back
        to God all that belongs to him.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 20:25
        content: "  Actual coins from that era have been found with the emperor\u2019s
          image and a superscription saying, \u201CTiberius Caesar Augustus, son
          of the divine Augustus.\u201D    "
    - name: '26: A Question about the Resurrection'
      title: A Question about the Resurrection
      number: 26
      content: The imposters were left speechless and amazed in the presence of all
        the people, unable to trap Jesus with his words.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Some of the Sadducees (a religious group that denies there is a resurrection
        of the dead) came to ask Jesus this question: '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CTeacher, the law of Moses [[COMMENT(0)]] teaches that if a
        man dies before he has children, his brother should marry the widow and raise
        up children for his brother\u2019s family line. "
      comments:
      - number: 20:28
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now suppose there was a family with seven brothers, and the oldest
        married and died without children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: 'Then his brother married the widow, and he too died with no children.
        And it continued to happen, one brother after another brother, until each
        of the seven had married the widow and died childless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: 'Then his brother married the widow, and he too died with no children.
        And it continued to happen, one brother after another brother, until each
        of the seven had married the widow and died childless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then finally, the widow died too. So here\u2019s our dilemma: "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Whose wife will the woman be when she\u2019s resurrected from the
        dead? Which of the brothers will be her husband, since all seven were once
        married to her?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CMarriage is meant for this world only.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35-36: '
      title: 
      number: 35-36
      content: "<JESUS>Those who are worthy of the resurrection from the dead into
        glory become immortal, like the angels, who never die nor marry. When the
        dead come to life again, they will be children of God\u2014the children of
        the resurrection.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35-36: '
      title: 
      number: 35-36
      content: "<JESUS>Those who are worthy of the resurrection from the dead into
        glory become immortal, like the angels, who never die nor marry. When the
        dead come to life again, they will be children of God\u2014the children of
        the resurrection.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>Even Moses taught the resurrection of the dead</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>when he wrote of the Lord God who was at the burning bush and said
        \u2018I am the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 20:37
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t you agree that God is not the God of the dead,
        but the God of the living? For in his eyes, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob are
        alive forevermore. He is the God who raises the dead.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "The experts of the law [[COMMENT(0)]] chimed in, \u201CYes, Teacher,
        you speak the truth beautifully.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 20:39
        content: "  Historically, these \u201Cexperts of the law\u201D (Pharisees)
          were opposed to, and argued with, the Sadducees over their disbelief of
          a supernatural resurrection.    "
    - name: '40: The Messiah, Both God and Man'
      title: The Messiah, Both God and Man
      number: 40
      content: From then on, the religious Sadducees never dared ask Jesus a question
        again.
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Jesus then posed this question to the people: <JESUS>\u201CHow can
        the experts of the law</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>say that Messiah is
        David\u2019s son?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 20:41
        content: "  Or \u201Cscribes,\u201D as translated from the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>Haven\u2019t you read in the Psalms where David himself wrote:</JESUS><JESUS>The
        Lord</JESUS>  <smallcaps><span class=\"ChapterContent_content__RrUqA\">Yahweh</span></smallcaps>Yahweh 
        <JESUS>said to my Lord,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><JESUS>\u2018Sit
        near me in the place of authority</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 20:42
        content: "  A Hebrew translation of this passage would read \u201Csaid to
          my Adonai.\u201D Paraphrased it would read \u201CThe Lord (God) said to
          my protecting Lord (Messiah).\u201D    "
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>until I subdue all your enemies under Your feet!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:43
        content: "  See  . Translated from the Aramaic and one Greek manuscript.
          Most Greek texts have \u201Cuntil all your enemies become a footstool under
          your feet.\u201D    "
    - name: '44: Jesus Denounces the Experts of the Law'
      title: Jesus Denounces the Experts of the Law
      number: 44
      content: "Jesus explained, <JESUS>\u201CIf David calls this one \u2018my Lord,\u2019
        how can he be his son?\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:44
        content: "  Jesus is challenging them to consider that the Christ will be
          both God and man (David\u2019s son and David\u2019s Lord).    "
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Within earshot of all the people, Jesus warned his disciples, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t follow the example of these pretentious experts
        of the law! They love to parade around in their religious garments so that
        people honor them wherever they go. They like to sit right up front in every
        meeting and push their way to the head table at every banquet.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>And for an offering they will pray long religious prayers
        at the homes of widows,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>cheating them out
        of their very livelihood. Beware of them all, because one day the Judge will
        strip them of honor, and judge them severely.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 20:47
        content: '  Translated from the Aramaic. The implication is that the religious
          leaders would go and pray at the homes of widows, then intimidate them
          and ask for offerings.  '
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Widow\u2019s Offering"
      title: "The Widow\u2019s Offering"
      number: 1
      content: 'Jesus observed all the wealthy coming into the temple courts wanting
        to be noticed as they came with their offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He noticed a very poor widow who dropped two small copper coins in
        the offering box. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CListen to me,\u201D</JESUS> he said. <JESUS>\u201CThis
        poor widow has given a larger offering than any of the wealthy.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Signs of the End of the Age'
      title: The Signs of the End of the Age
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>For the rich only gave out of their surplus, but she sacrificed
        out of her poverty and gave to God all that she had to live on.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Some of the disciples remarked about the beauty of the temple. They
        pointed out all the lovely adornments and how it was built with excellence
        from the gifts given to God.Jesus said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe day of utter destruction will come to everything
        you admire here. It will all become a heap of rubble!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CMaster, tell us,\u201D they asked, \u201Cwhen exactly will
        this happen? Can you tell us what warning sign to look for when it is about
        to take place?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CDeception will run rampant and many
        will appear on the scene, saying I have sent them, or saying about themselves,
        \u2018I am the Messiah!\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>These doomsday
        deceivers will say, \u2018The end of the age is now here!\u2019 But listen
        to me. Don\u2019t let any of these imposters fool you.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 21:8
        content: "  Translated from the Aramaic, where it literally states, \u201CI
          Am! The Messiah!\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThere will also be many wars and revolutions on every
        side, with rumors of more wars to come. Don\u2019t panic or give in to your
        fears, for these things are bound to happen. This is still not the end yet.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>There will be upheavals
        of every kind.</JESUS>  <JESUS>Nations will go to war against each other,
        and kingdom against kingdom.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>There will be terrible earthquakes and seismic events of epic
        proportion that result in famines in one place after another. There will
        be horrible plagues and epidemics, cataclysmic storms</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>on the earth, and astonishing signs and cosmic disturbances in the
        heavens. But before all of this happens, you will be hunted down and arrested,
        persecuted by both civil and religious authorities, and thrown into prison.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 21:11
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Only one Greek manuscript adds,
          \u201Cgreat storms.\u201D    "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: '<JESUS>And because you follow me, you will be on trial before kings
        and governmental leaders as an opportunity to testify to them in my name.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: '<JESUS>And because you follow me, you will be on trial before kings
        and governmental leaders as an opportunity to testify to them in my name.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: <JESUS>Yet determine in your hearts not to prepare for your own defense.
        Simply speak with the words of wisdom that I will give you that moment, and
        none of your persecutors will be able to withstand the grace and wisdom that
        comes from your mouths.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: <JESUS>Yet determine in your hearts not to prepare for your own defense.
        Simply speak with the words of wisdom that I will give you that moment, and
        none of your persecutors will be able to withstand the grace and wisdom that
        comes from your mouths.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou can expect betrayal even by your parents, your brothers,
        your relatives and friends\u2014and yes, some of you will die as martyrs.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>You will be hated by all because</JESUS>  <JESUS>of my life
        in you.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 21:17
        content: "  The Greek says, \u201Cbecause of my name.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>But don\u2019t worry. My grace will never desert you or depart
        from your life.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 21:18
        content: "  Although quite different from the Greek manuscripts, this is
          the literal translation of the Aramaic figure of speech, \u201CGrace will
          not leave your head.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: The Destruction of Jerusalem'
      title: The Destruction of Jerusalem
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Stand firm with patient endurance and you will find your souls\u2019
        deliverance.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhen you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, you will
        know for sure that its devastation is imminent.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 21:20
        content: "  This was fulfilled in AD 70 when the Roman armies sacked Jerusalem.
          Some historians estimate that the Romans slaughtered more than one million
          Jews at that time and took captive up to one hundred thousand to other
          nations. Jews today still mourn the destruction of the temple on the fast
          of Tisha B\u2019Av, the ninth day of the fifth month.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>At that time all who are living in Judea must flee to the
        mountains. Those who live inside the city gates, leave and flee, and those
        who live outside the city must not enter it seeking refuge.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>For these will be the days of God\u2019s vengeance to fulfill
        what has been written</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>against Jerusalem.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 21:22
        content: '  See  ;  ;  ;  . The book of Lamentations expresses grief over
          the loss of the city and the temple.    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>It will be extremely difficult for pregnant women and for
        those nursing little ones in that day, for great persecution and wrath will
        rise against this nation.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Coming of the Son of Man'
      title: The Coming of the Son of Man
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Many will be cut down by the sword or scattered as prisoners
        to many countries. And Jerusalem shall be trampled down by nations until
        the days of world empires come to an end.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CExpect to witness amazing and perplexing signs with
        the sun, the moon, and the stars.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>The raging
        of the sea will bring desperation and turmoil to many nations.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 21:25
        content: '  See  ;  ;  .    '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: <JESUS>Earthquakes</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will bring panic
        and disaster. What men see coming to the earth will cause the fear of doom
        to grip their hearts, for they will even see the powers of the heavenly realm
        shaken!</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 21:26
        content: '  The word    is found only in Aramaic manuscripts.    '
    - name: '27-28: The Lesson of the Fig Tree'
      title: The Lesson of the Fig Tree
      number: 27-28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd at last, when you see how the Son of Man</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>comes\u2014surrounded with a cloud, with great power
        and miracles, in the radiance of his splendor, and with great glory and praises</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>\u2014it will make you jump for joy! For the time of your full transformation</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>has arrived.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "21:27\u201328"
        content: "  The title \u201CSon of Man\u201D was used frequently when Jesus
          spoke of himself. Note that he is not the \u201Cson of a man,\u201D but
          the Son of God who became a man.      \u201CPraises\u201D is only found
          in Aramaic manuscripts.      The Greek word is \u201Credemption\u201D or
          \u201Cliberation.\u201D It speaks of the total transformation of our body,
          soul, and spirit when we see him as he is ().    "
    - name: '27-28: The Lesson of the Fig Tree'
      title: The Lesson of the Fig Tree
      number: 27-28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd at last, when you see how the Son of Man</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>comes\u2014surrounded with a cloud, with great power
        and miracles, in the radiance of his splendor, and with great glory and praises</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>\u2014it will make you jump for joy! For the time of your full transformation</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>has arrived.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "21:27\u201328"
        content: "  The title \u201CSon of Man\u201D was used frequently when Jesus
          spoke of himself. Note that he is not the \u201Cson of a man,\u201D but
          the Son of God who became a man.      \u201CPraises\u201D is only found
          in Aramaic manuscripts.      The Greek word is \u201Credemption\u201D or
          \u201Cliberation.\u201D It speaks of the total transformation of our body,
          soul, and spirit when we see him as he is ().    "
    - name: '29-30: '
      title: 
      number: 29-30
      content: "Jesus gave his disciples this parable:<JESUS>\u201CHaven\u2019t you
        observed that when the fig tree, or any tree, buds and blooms, the season
        is changing and summer is near?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29-30: '
      title: 
      number: 29-30
      content: "Jesus gave his disciples this parable:<JESUS>\u201CHaven\u2019t you
        observed that when the fig tree, or any tree, buds and blooms, the season
        is changing and summer is near?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>In the same way, when you see these prophetic signs occurring,
        you realize the earth is yielding to</JESUS>  <JESUS>the fullness of</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>God\u2019s kingdom.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>I assure you, the end of this age will not come until all
        I have spoken has come to pass.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Guard Your Hearts'
      title: Guard Your Hearts
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>Earth and sky will wear out and fade away before one word
        I speak loses its power or fails to accomplish its purpose.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBe careful that you never allow your hearts to grow
        cold. Be careful that you are not caught off guard,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>or your hearts will be weighed down with carousing, drunkenness, and
        the worries of this life, and that day will come upon you suddenly like a
        trap. Don\u2019t let me come and find you drunk or living carelessly like
        everyone else.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 21:34
        content: "  The Aramaic text says, \u201CBeware that your hearts never grow
          cold.\u201D    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>For that day will come as a shocking surprise to all.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>Keep a constant watch over your soul, and pray for the courage
        and grace to prevail over these things that are destined to occur and that
        you will stand before the presence of the Son of Man</JESUS>  <JESUS>with
        a clear conscience</JESUS><JESUS>.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Each day, Jesus taught in the temple and spent his nights on the
        Mount of Olives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: And all the people came early to the temple courts to listen to the
        words [[COMMENT(0)]] he taught.
      comments:
      - number: 21:38
        content: '  The Greek text is  .  '
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: Satan Entered into Judas'
      title: Satan Entered into Judas
      number: 1-2
      content: "As the celebration of the Passover Lamb [[COMMENT(0)]] was approaching,
        the Jewish religious leaders and scholars of the law continually schemed
        to find a way to murder Jesus without starting a riot\u2014for they feared
        the crowds."
      comments:
      - number: "22:1\u20132"
        content: "  The Passover celebration was known as the \u201CFeast of Bread
          without Yeast.\u201D The Jewish people commemorate their exodus from Egypt
          to this day with a weeklong Passover feast. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '1-2: Satan Entered into Judas'
      title: Satan Entered into Judas
      number: 1-2
      content: "As the celebration of the Passover Lamb [[COMMENT(0)]] was approaching,
        the Jewish religious leaders and scholars of the law continually schemed
        to find a way to murder Jesus without starting a riot\u2014for they feared
        the crowds."
      comments:
      - number: "22:1\u20132"
        content: "  The Passover celebration was known as the \u201CFeast of Bread
          without Yeast.\u201D The Jewish people commemorate their exodus from Egypt
          to this day with a weeklong Passover feast. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'At that time Satan himself entered into Judas the locksmith, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        who was one of the twelve apostles. '
      comments:
      - number: 22:3
        content: '  See the last footnote on  .    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He secretly went to the religious hierarchy and the captains of the
        temple guards to discuss with them how he could betray Jesus and turn him
        over to their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The religious hierarchy was elated over Judas\u2019 treachery, and
        they agreed to give him a sum of money in exchange for Jesus\u2019 betrayal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Jesus Prophesies the Location of the Last Supper'
      title: Jesus Prophesies the Location of the Last Supper
      number: 6
      content: Judas vowed that he would find them a suitable opportunity to betray
        Jesus when he was away from the crowds.
      comments: []
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "On the day the Passover lambs were to be sacrificed, Jesus sent for
        Peter and John and instructed them, <JESUS>\u201CGo and prepare the Passover
        supper so we can eat it together.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '7-8: '
      title: 
      number: 7-8
      content: "On the day the Passover lambs were to be sacrificed, Jesus sent for
        Peter and John and instructed them, <JESUS>\u201CGo and prepare the Passover
        supper so we can eat it together.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They asked him, \u201CWhere do we make the preparations to eat the
        meal?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus gave them this sign: <JESUS>\u201CWhen you enter the city,
        you will find a man</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>carrying a jug of water.</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>Follow him home</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 22:10
        content: "  Carrying water was a task given to women; it would have been
          easy to spot a man carrying the water jug.      Jerusalem would have been
          filled with pilgrims coming to celebrate the feast. Every house would be
          filled with additional guests, so finding a room for Jesus and the Twelve
          would be no easy task. It is possible that this man carrying a jug of water
          (normally a woman\u2019s task) would be an Essene. They were the only Jewish
          men who culturally would carry water in this way since they were celibates.
          They had a community in Jerusalem that had a gate called the \u201CEssene
          Gate.\u201D They also had a different calendar than the typical Jewish
          one, which meant they would still have guest rooms available.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>and say to the owner of the house, \u2018The Teacher told
        us to ask you, \u201CWhere is the room I may use to have the Passover meal
        with my disciples?\u201D&nbsp;\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>He will then take you to a large, fully furnished upstairs
        room. Make the preparations for us there.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jesus and His Disciples Eat the Last Supper'
      title: Jesus and His Disciples Eat the Last Supper
      number: 13
      content: They went and found everything to be exactly like Jesus had prophesied,
        and they prepared the Passover meal.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Jesus arrived at the upper room, he took his place at the table
        along with all the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he told them, <JESUS>\u201CI have longed with passion and desire
        to eat this Passover lamb with you before I endure my sufferings.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>I promise you that the next time we eat this, we will be together
        in the feast of God\u2019s kingdom.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he raised a cup and gave thanks to God and said to them, <JESUS>\u201CTake
        this and pass it on to one another and drink.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I promise you that the next time we drink this wine, we will
        be together in the feast of God\u2019s kingdom.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:18
        content: "  Verses    are not found in most Aramaic texts. Most Greek texts
          and a fifth-century Aramaic manuscript known as \u201Cthe Palestinian Syriac\u201D
          include them in the narrative.    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he lifted up a loaf, and after praying a prayer of thanksgiving
        to God, he gave each of his apostles a piece of bread, saying, <JESUS>\u201CThis
        loaf is my body,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>which is now being offered
        to you. Always eat it to remember me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 22:19
        content: "  From here to the end of v.    is considered the most highly debated
          passage in Luke\u2019s Gospel because a few reliable Greek manuscripts
          do not have it. Yet there is ample internal evidence to argue for its inclusion.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "After supper was over, he lifted the cup again and said, <JESUS>\u201CThis
        cup is my blood of the new covenant</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I make
        with you, and it will be poured out soon for all of you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 22:20
        content: "  The Aramaic word used here is literally \u201Cnew testament.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>But I want you to know that the hands of the one who delivers
        me to be the sacrifice are with mine on the table this very moment.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>The Son of Man must now go where he will be sacrificed. But
        there will be great and unending doom for the man who betrays me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Apostles Argue over Which of Them Will Be the Greatest'
      title: Apostles Argue over Which of Them Will Be the Greatest
      number: 23
      content: The apostles questioned among themselves which one of them was about
        to do this.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The disciples bickered over which one of them would be considered
        the greatest [[COMMENT(0)]] in the kingdom. '
      comments:
      - number: 22:24
        content: "  This took place at the Lord\u2019s Passover table. Their discussion
          of who was the worst among them led them to argue over who was the greatest.
          Jesus was only hours away from the horrible death of crucifixion while
          his apostles argued.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus interrupted their argument, saying, <JESUS>\u201CThe kings
        and men of authority in this world rule oppressively over their subjects,
        claiming that they do it for the good of the people. They are obsessed with
        how others see them.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 22:25
        content: "  The Aramaic is actually \u201CThey want to be called \u2018servants
          of goodness.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>But this is not your calling. You will lead by a different
        model. The greatest one among you will live as one called to serve others
        without honor.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>The greatest honor and authority
        is reserved for the one who has a servant heart.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 22:26
        content: "  The Greek text uses the word here for \u201Cyoungest,\u201D and
          the Aramaic is \u201Csmall one.\u201D In Hebrew culture in the days of
          Jesus, the firstborn of the household had honor, while the youngest accepted
          the role of menial service to all the others of the house.    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: <JESUS>The leaders who are served are the most important in your eyes,
        but in the kingdom, it is the servants who lead. Am I not here with you as
        one who serves?</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBecause you have stood with me through all my trials
        and ordeals,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>I am promising you the kingdom that the Father has promised
        me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jesus Prophesies Peter\u2019s Denial"
      title: "Jesus Prophesies Peter\u2019s Denial"
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>We will celebrate in this kingdom and you will feast with
        me at my table. And each of you will be given a throne, twelve thrones in
        all, and you will be made rulers on thrones to judge the tribes of Israel.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CPeter, my dear friend, listen to what I\u2019m about
        to tell you. Satan has obtained permission to come and sift you all like
        wheat and test your faith.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>But I have prayed for you, Peter, that you would stay faithful
        to me no matter what comes. Remember this: after you have turned back to
        me and have been restored, make it your life mission to strengthen the faith
        of your brothers.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CBut Lord,\u201D Peter replied, \u201CI am ready to stand with
        you to the very end, even if it means prison or death!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus looked at him and prophesied, <JESUS>\u201CBefore the rooster
        crows in the morning, you will deny</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>three
        times that you even know me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 22:34
        content: "  The Aramaic text says \u201Cblasphemed.\u201D    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then he said to all of them, <JESUS>\u201CWhen I sent you out empty-handed,
        did you lack anything?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CNot a thing,\u201D they answered.
        \u201CGod provided all we needed.\u201DJesus said, <JESUS>\u201CBut now I
        say to you: Take what you need.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>If you have money, take it</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u2014and
        a knapsack and a sword.</JESUS>    <JESUS>Danger is imminent.</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 22:36
        content: "  Now the disciples were to take needed items with them, including
          money, for they were to be a source of blessing to others with their generosity.     
          It is possible that Jesus was using symbolic speech, for we take with us
          the sword of the Spirit, which is the Word of God. See  .      The text
          here is a Hebraic figure of speech: \u201CIf you don\u2019t have a sword,
          you\u2019d better sell something and buy one,\u201D which implies that
          danger is imminent.    "
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>For the prophetic Scripture about me \u2018He will be accused
        of being a criminal\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will now come to
        pass. All that was prophesied of me will be fulfilled.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 22:37
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '38: The Garden of Gethsemane'
      title: The Garden of Gethsemane
      number: 38
      content: "The disciples told him, \u201CLord, we already have two swords!\u201D<JESUS>\u201CYou
        still don\u2019t understand,\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus responded."
      comments:
      - number: 22:38
        content: "  Or \u201CThat will be enough.\u201D Jesus is saying, \u201CNever
          mind. You still don\u2019t get it.\u201D He corrected their thinking about
          taking swords and using violent means in vv.  .    "
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Jesus left the upper room with his disciples [[COMMENT(0)]] and,
        as was his habit, went to the Mount of Olives, his place of secret prayer. '
      comments:
      - number: 22:39
        content: '  That is, with the exception of Judas. See v.  .    '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "There he told the apostles, <JESUS>\u201CKeep praying for strength
        to be spared from the severe test of your faith that is about to come.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then he withdrew from them a short distance [[COMMENT(0)]] to be
        alone. Kneeling down, he prayed, '
      comments:
      - number: 22:41
        content: "  Literally \u201Ca stone\u2019s throw away.\u201D    "
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CFather, if you are willing, take this cup of agony away
        from me.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>But no matter what, your will must
        be mine.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 22:42
        content: '  Jesus asked the Father to be spared from death in the garden
          so that he could go all the way to the cross. His prayer was answered.
          The blood that dripped in the garden would not redeem. Jesus had to carry
          the cross and fulfill all that was written of him. See  .    '
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Jesus called [[COMMENT(0)]] for an angel of glory to strengthen him,
        and the angel appeared. '
      comments:
      - number: 22:43
        content: "  Translated from the Aramaic text. The Greek manuscripts state
          it passively: \u201CAn angel from heaven appeared.\u201D    "
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'He prayed even more passionately, like one being sacrificed, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        until he was in such intense agony of spirit that his sweat became drops
        of blood, dripping onto the ground. '
      comments:
      - number: 22:44
        content: "  The Aramaic text is literally \u201CHe prayed sacrificially.\u201D     
          Although vv.    are found in the Aramaic manuscript, many Greek texts omit
          them. Most of the early church fathers included them in their translations
          and commentaries. Though very rare, the phenomenon of hematidrosis, sweating
          blood, is well documented. Under great emotional stress, tiny capillaries
          in the sweat glands can break, thus mixing blood with sweat. This process
          could have marked weakness and possibly shock.    "
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'When Jesus finished praying, he got up and went to his disciples
        and found them all asleep, for they were exhausted and overwhelmed with sorrow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: Judas Betrays Jesus'
      title: Judas Betrays Jesus
      number: 46
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CWhy are you sleeping?\u201D</JESUS> he asked them. <JESUS>\u201CYou
        need to be alert and pray for the strength to endure the great temptation.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "No sooner had he finished speaking when suddenly a mob approached,
        and in front of the mob was his disciple Judas. He walked up close to Jesus
        and greeted him with a kiss. For he had agreed to give the religious leaders
        a sign, saying, \u201CThe one I kiss is the one to seize.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:47
        content: '  Nearly every Greek manuscript leaves out this information. The
          Aramaic text includes it.    '
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Jesus looked at him with sorrow and said, <JESUS>\u201CA kiss, Judas?
        Are you really going to betray the Son of Man with a kiss?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "When the other disciples understood what was happening, they asked,
        \u201CLord, shall we fight them with our swords?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Just then, one of the disciples swung his sword at the high priest\u2019s
        servant and slashed off his right ear. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:50
        content: "  The servant\u2019s name was Malchus (). What Peter did was a
          criminal act that could have ruined his entire life. Jesus was concerned
          both for the wounded man and Peter\u2019s future.    "
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Jesus stopped the incident from escalating any further by saying,
        <JESUS>\u201CEnough of this!\u201D</JESUS> Then he touched the right side
        of the injured man\u2019s head and the ear grew back  [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014he
        was healed!"
      comments:
      - number: 22:51
        content: '  Implied in the context of this miracle. Jesus, the Creator, re-created
          his ear. The last thing Jesus did before they tied and bound his beautiful
          hands to arrest him in Gethsemane: He used his healing hands to restore
          the cut-off ear that Peter slashed (here and  ). He was bound for hours
          until they loosed his hands to pierce them with nails.    '
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Jesus turned to those who had come to seize him\u2014the ruling priests,
        the officers of the temple police, and the religious leaders\u2014and said,
        <JESUS>\u201CAm I a criminal that you come to capture me with clubs and swords?
        Wasn\u2019t I with you day after day, teaching in the temple courts?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: Peter Denies He Knew Jesus'
      title: Peter Denies He Knew Jesus
      number: 53
      content: "<JESUS>You could have seized me at any time. But in the darkness
        of night you have now found your time, for it belongs to you and to the prince
        of darkness.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 22:53
        content: "  The \u201Cprince of darkness\u201D is Satan. This phrase is found
          only in the Aramaic manuscripts. The Greek text states, \u201Cthe powers
          of darkness.\u201D    "
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The religious leaders seized Jesus and led him away, but Peter followed
        from a safe distance. They brought him to the home of the high priest, where
        people were already gathered out in the courtyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: Someone had built a fire, so Peter inched closer and sat down among
        them to stay warm.
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "A girl noticed Peter sitting in the firelight. Staring at him, she
        pointed him out and said, \u201CThis man is one of Jesus\u2019 disciples!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "Peter flatly denied it, saying, \u201CWhat are you talking about,
        girl? I don\u2019t know him!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "A little while later, someone else spotted Peter and said, \u201CI
        recognize you. You\u2019re one of his, I know it!\u201DPeter again said,
        \u201CI\u2019m not one of his disciples.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "About an hour later, someone else identified Peter and insisted he
        was a disciple of Jesus, saying, \u201CLook at him! He\u2019s from Galilee,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] just like Jesus. I know he\u2019s one of them.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 22:59
        content: "  Peter\u2019s accent gave him away as being a Galilean. See also 
          .    "
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "But Peter was adamant. \u201CListen, I don\u2019t know what you\u2019re
        talking about. Don\u2019t you understand? I don\u2019t even know him.\u201D
        While the words were still in his mouth, the rooster crowed."
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "At that moment, the Lord, who was being led through the courtyard
        by his captors, [[COMMENT(0)]] turned around and gazed at Peter. All at once
        Peter remembered the words Jesus had prophesied over him, <JESUS>\u201CBefore
        the rooster crows in the morning, you will deny three times that you even
        know me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 22:61
        content: '  Implied by the context, necessary for proper understanding of
          the narrative.    '
    - name: '62: Jesus Is Mocked and Severely Beaten'
      title: Jesus Is Mocked and Severely Beaten
      number: 62
      content: Peter burst into tears, [[COMMENT(0)]] ran off from the crowd, and
        wept bitterly.
      comments:
      - number: 22:62
        content: '  It is not just our sin that causes us to weep. It is seeing the
          Savior whom we have sinned against that brings our tears.    '
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Those who were guarding Jesus mocked and beat him severely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "They also made fun of him, blindfolding him and slapping his face
        and saying, \u201CProve that you are a prophet and tell us which one of us
        hit you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '65: Jesus before the Jewish Council'
      title: Jesus before the Jewish Council
      number: 65
      content: They blasphemed and heaped insult after insult upon him.
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'At daybreak the high priests, the experts of the law, and the top
        religious leaders convened and had Jesus brought before their council. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "They asked him point blank, \u201CTell us, are you the Christ, the
        Messiah, or not?\u201DJesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CIf I tell you the truth,
        you won\u2019t believe me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: '<JESUS>And if I question you, you will not answer me or release me.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 22:68
        content: "  The phrase \u201Cor release me\u201D is found only in the Aramaic
          text.  "
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: "<JESUS>But from today on, the Son of Man will be enthroned in the
        place of honor, power, and authority with Almighty God.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "They all shouted, \u201CThen you do claim to be the Son of God?\u201DHe
        said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou are the ones who say I am.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: "They all shouted, \u201CWe\u2019ve heard it from his very lips! What
        further proof do we need?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus before Pilate'
      title: Jesus before Pilate
      number: 1
      content: 'The entire council stood at once and took Jesus to Pilate, the Roman
        governor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They accused him of false testimony, saying, \u201CThis man tells
        us not to pay our taxes to Caesar. And he proclaims himself to be Christ
        the King and Messiah. He\u2019s a deceiver of our nation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Pilate asked Jesus, \u201CIs this true? Are you their king and Messiah?\u201DJesus
        answered, <JESUS>\u201CIt is true.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Pilate turned to the high priests and to the gathered crowd and said,
        \u201CThis man has committed no crime. I find nothing wrong with him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Jesus before Herod'
      title: Jesus before Herod
      number: 5
      content: "But they yelled and demanded that Pilate do something, saying, \u201CHe
        has stirred up our nation, misleading people from the moment he began teaching
        in Galilee until he has come here to Jerusalem!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "When Pilate heard the word Galilee, he asked if Jesus was a Galilean,
        and when they told him \u201Cyes,\u201D Pilate saw a way out of his problem.
        He knew that Antipas, [[COMMENT(0)]] son of Herod, ruled over Galilee, and
        he happened to be in Jerusalem at that time, so Pilate sent Jesus to Antipas."
      comments:
      - number: "23:6\u20137"
        content: "  \u201CAntipas\u201D is a nickname for Herod Antipater, son of
          Herod the Great. The Greek text reads simply \u201CHerod.\u201D    "
    - name: '6-7: '
      title: 
      number: 6-7
      content: "When Pilate heard the word Galilee, he asked if Jesus was a Galilean,
        and when they told him \u201Cyes,\u201D Pilate saw a way out of his problem.
        He knew that Antipas, [[COMMENT(0)]] son of Herod, ruled over Galilee, and
        he happened to be in Jerusalem at that time, so Pilate sent Jesus to Antipas."
      comments:
      - number: "23:6\u20137"
        content: "  \u201CAntipas\u201D is a nickname for Herod Antipater, son of
          Herod the Great. The Greek text reads simply \u201CHerod.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When he saw Jesus, he was elated, for he had heard a great deal about
        his ministry and wanted Jesus to perform a miracle in front of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Antipas questioned him at length, but Jesus wouldn\u2019t even answer
        him."
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: 'All the while the high priests and religious leaders stood by, accusing
        Jesus of wrongdoing, so that Antipas and his soldiers treated him with scorn
        and mocking. Antipas put an elegant purple robe on Jesus and sent him back
        to Pilate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10-11: '
      title: 
      number: 10-11
      content: 'All the while the high priests and religious leaders stood by, accusing
        Jesus of wrongdoing, so that Antipas and his soldiers treated him with scorn
        and mocking. Antipas put an elegant purple robe on Jesus and sent him back
        to Pilate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Jesus Sentenced to Death'
      title: Jesus Sentenced to Death
      number: 12
      content: That day, Antipas and Pilate healed their long-standing feud and they
        became good friends.
      comments: []
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "Pilate gathered together the people, the high priests, and all the
        religious leaders of the nation. [[COMMENT(0)]] He told them, \u201CYou have
        presented this man to me and charged him with stirring a rebellion among
        the people. I have examined him here in your presence and have put him on
        trial. My verdict is that none of your charges against him are true. I find
        no fault in him.   "
      comments:
      - number: "23:13\u201314"
        content: "  This group of religious leaders was known as the Jewish council
          of the Sanhedrin.      The phrase \u201CI find no fault in him\u201D is
          found in the Aramaic text.    "
    - name: '13-14: '
      title: 
      number: 13-14
      content: "Pilate gathered together the people, the high priests, and all the
        religious leaders of the nation. [[COMMENT(0)]] He told them, \u201CYou have
        presented this man to me and charged him with stirring a rebellion among
        the people. I have examined him here in your presence and have put him on
        trial. My verdict is that none of your charges against him are true. I find
        no fault in him.   "
      comments:
      - number: "23:13\u201314"
        content: "  This group of religious leaders was known as the Jewish council
          of the Sanhedrin.      The phrase \u201CI find no fault in him\u201D is
          found in the Aramaic text.    "
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: "Then I sent him to Antipas, son of Herod, who questioned him and
        found him not guilty. Since he has done nothing deserving of death, I have
        decided to punish him with a severe flogging and release him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15-16: '
      title: 
      number: 15-16
      content: "Then I sent him to Antipas, son of Herod, who questioned him and
        found him not guilty. Since he has done nothing deserving of death, I have
        decided to punish him with a severe flogging and release him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For it was Pilate\u2019s custom to honor the Jewish holiday by releasing
        a prisoner. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 23:17
        content: '  Although many Greek manuscripts do not have this verse in the
          text, it is found in the Aramaic text.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When the crowd heard this, they went wild. Erupting with anger, they
        cried out, \u201CNo! Take this one away and release Barabbas!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 23:18
        content: "  There were two men, two sons. Barabbas means \u201Cson of a father.\u201D
          Jesus was the Son of our heavenly Father. One was a son of Adam; the other
          was the Son of God.    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: For Barabbas had been thrown in prison for robbery [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and murder.
      comments:
      - number: 23:19
        content: "  Most Greek manuscripts have \u201Cfor insurrection.\u201D The
          Aramaic states \u201Cfor robbery.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Pilate, wanting to release Jesus, tried to convince them it was best
        to let Jesus go, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but they screamed out over and over, \u201CCrucify him! Crucify him!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 23:21
        content: '  Crucifixion was the cruelest form of execution, reserved for
          only the worst of criminals.    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A third time, Pilate asked the crowd, \u201CWhat evil crime has this
        man committed that I should have him crucified? I haven\u2019t found one
        thing that warrants a death sentence! I will have him flogged severely and
        then release him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But the people and the high priests, shouting like a mob, screamed
        out at the top of their lungs, \u201CNo! Crucify him! Crucify him!\u201DFinally
        their shouts and screams succeeded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Pilate caved in to the crowd and ordered that the will of the people
        be done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: The Crucifixion of Jesus'
      title: The Crucifixion of Jesus
      number: 25
      content: Then he released the guilty murderer Barabbas, as they had insisted,
        and handed Jesus over to be crucified.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "As the guards led Jesus to be crucified, there was an African man
        in the crowd named Simon, from Libya. [[COMMENT(0)]] He had just arrived
        from a rural village to keep the Feast of the Passover. The guards laid Jesus\u2019
        cross on Simon\u2019s shoulders  and forced him to walk behind Jesus, carrying
        his cross."
      comments:
      - number: 23:26
        content: "  Or \u201Cfrom Cyrene,\u201D which is present-day Tripoli, Libya.     
          By this time Jesus had been severely beaten and flogged, had gone days
          without sleep, and was carrying a heavy load.    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Massive crowds gathered to follow Jesus, including a number of women,
        who were wailing with sorrow over him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jesus turned to them and said, <JESUS>\u201CDaughters of Jerusalem,
        do not weep for me. You should be weeping for yourselves and your children.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>The day is coming when it will not be the women with children
        who are blessed but those who are childless. Then you will say, \u2018The
        barren women are the most fortunate! Those who have never given birth and
        never nursed a child\u2014</JESUS><JESUS>they are more fortunate than we,
        for they will never see their children put to death</JESUS><JESUS>!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>And the people will cry out for the mountains and hills to
        fall on top of them to hide them from all that is to come.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 23:30
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>For if this is what they do to the living Branch, what will
        they do with the dead ones?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The guards led away two criminals with Jesus, to execute all three
        at the same time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When they came to the place that is known as The Skull, the guards
        crucified Jesus, nailing him on the center cross between the two criminals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "While they were nailing Jesus to the cross, he prayed over and over,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u201CFather, forgive them,</JESUS>    <JESUS>for
        they don\u2019t know what they\u2019re doing.\u201D</JESUS>The soldiers,
        after they crucified him, gambled over his clothing."
      comments:
      - number: 23:34
        content: "  Or \u201Che prayed intensely.\u201D      The Greek text implies
          a repetitive action. He did not pray, \u201Cforgive me,\u201D but \u201Cforgive
          them.\u201D As the centurion crushed him to the ground and tied his arms
          to the crossbeam, Jesus prayed, \u201CFather, forgive them.\u201D When
          the spikes tore through each quivering palm, he prayed again, \u201CFather,
          forgive them.\u201D And when the soldiers parted his garments and gambled
          for the seamless robe, again Jesus prayed, \u201CFather, forgive them.\u201D
          Only heaven knows how many times he uttered that prayer. Many reliable
          Greek manuscripts omit this verse; however, it does fit with the Lukan
          theology of forgiveness () and the parallel passage in  .    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "A great crowd gathered to watch what was happening. The religious
        leaders sneered at Jesus and mocked him, saying, \u201CLook at this man!
        What kind of \u2018chosen Messiah\u2019 is this? He pretended to save others,
        but he can\u2019t even save himself!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: The soldiers joined in the mockery, offering Jesus a drink of vinegar.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 23:36
        content: '  See  . It was likely Jesus had had nothing to drink since the
          night before.    '
    - name: '37-38: '
      title: 
      number: 37-38
      content: "Over Jesus\u2019 head on the cross was written an inscription in
        Greek, Latin, and Aramaic: [[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CThis man is the king of all
        the Jews.\u201D And all the soldiers laughed and scoffed at him, saying,
        \u201CHey! If you\u2019re the king of Jews, why don\u2019t you save yourself?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "23:37\u201338"
        content: '  Many Greek texts omit the mention of these three languages.    '
    - name: '37-38: '
      title: 
      number: 37-38
      content: "Over Jesus\u2019 head on the cross was written an inscription in
        Greek, Latin, and Aramaic: [[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CThis man is the king of all
        the Jews.\u201D And all the soldiers laughed and scoffed at him, saying,
        \u201CHey! If you\u2019re the king of Jews, why don\u2019t you save yourself?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "23:37\u201338"
        content: '  Many Greek texts omit the mention of these three languages.    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "One of the criminals hanging on the cross next to Jesus kept ridiculing
        him, saying, \u201CWhat kind of Messiah are you? Save yourself and save us
        from this death!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "The criminal hanging on the other cross rebuked the man, saying,
        \u201CDon\u2019t you fear God? You\u2019re about to die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "We deserve to be condemned. We\u2019re just being repaid for what
        we\u2019ve done. But this man\u2014he\u2019s done nothing wrong!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI beg of you, Jesus, show me grace and take me
        with you into your everlasting kingdom!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '43: The Death of the Savior'
      title: The Death of the Savior
      number: 43
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CI promise you\u2014this very day you
        will enter paradise with me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'It was now only midday, yet the whole world became dark for three
        hours as the light of the sun faded away. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 23:44
        content: "  The darkening of the sun indicated that the \u201Cday of the
          Lord\u201D had now come. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And suddenly in the temple the thick veil hanging in the Holy Place
        was ripped in two! '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Then Jesus cried out with a loud voice, <JESUS>\u201CFather, I surrender
        my Spirit into your hands.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] And he took his
        last breath and died."
      comments:
      - number: 23:46
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "When the Roman captain overseeing the crucifixion witnessed all that
        took place, he was awestruck and glorified God. Acknowledging what they had
        done, he said, \u201CI have no doubt; we just killed the righteous one.\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 23:47
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek is \u201Cinnocent man.\u201D    "
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'The crowds that had gathered to observe this spectacle went back
        to their homes, overcome with deep sorrow [[COMMENT(0)]] and devastated by
        what they had witnessed. '
      comments:
      - number: 23:48
        content: "  Literally \u201Cbeating their breasts,\u201D which is a figure
          of speech for deep sorrow.    "
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: But standing off at a distance were some who truly knew Jesus, and
        the women who had followed him all the way from Galilee were keeping vigil.
      comments: []
    - name: '50-51: '
      title: 
      number: 50-51
      content: "There was also a member of the Jewish council named Joseph, from
        the village of Ramah, [[COMMENT(0)]] a good-hearted, honorable man who was
        eager for God\u2019s kingdom to appear. He had strongly disagreed with the
        decision of the council to crucify Jesus.   "
      comments:
      - number: "23:50\u201351"
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Ramah (formerly Ramathaim Zophim)
          was the village of Samuel, only a few miles from Jerusalem. The Greek is,
          \u201CJoseph of Arimathea.\u201D      One ancient Syriac manuscript adds
          here, \u201CThis man was one who did not take part with the mind of the
          devil.\u201D  "
    - name: '50-51: '
      title: 
      number: 50-51
      content: "There was also a member of the Jewish council named Joseph, from
        the village of Ramah, [[COMMENT(0)]] a good-hearted, honorable man who was
        eager for God\u2019s kingdom to appear. He had strongly disagreed with the
        decision of the council to crucify Jesus.   "
      comments:
      - number: "23:50\u201351"
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Ramah (formerly Ramathaim Zophim)
          was the village of Samuel, only a few miles from Jerusalem. The Greek is,
          \u201CJoseph of Arimathea.\u201D      One ancient Syriac manuscript adds
          here, \u201CThis man was one who did not take part with the mind of the
          devil.\u201D  "
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'He came before Pilate and asked permission to take the body of Jesus
        for a proper burial, and Pilate granted his request. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'So he took the body from the cross, wrapped it in a winding sheet
        of linen, and placed it in a new, unused tomb chiseled out of solid rock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: It was Preparation Day, and the Sabbath was fast approaching.
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'The women who had been companions of Jesus from the beginning saw
        all this take place and carefully contemplated how the body was laid in the
        tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: Afterward they returned home and prepared fragrant spices and ointments
        and were planning to anoint his body after the Sabbath was completed, according
        to the commandments of the law.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Resurrection of Jesus'
      title: The Resurrection of Jesus
      number: 1
      content: 'Very early that Sunday morning, the women made their way to the tomb,
        carrying the spices they had prepared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Among them were Mary Magdalene, Joanna, and Jesus\u2019 mother Mary.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 24:1
        content: '  For the sake of the English narrative, the information found
          in v.    is placed here.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Arriving at the tomb they discovered that the huge stone covering
        the entrance had been rolled aside, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: so they went in to look. But the tomb was empty. The body of Jesus
        was gone!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They stood there, stunned and perplexed. Suddenly, two men appeared
        above them in dazzling white robes shining like lightning. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 24:4
        content: "  \u201CAbove them\u201D is found only in the Aramaic text.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Terrified, the women fell to the ground on their faces.The men in
        white said to them, \u201CWhy would you look for the Living One [[COMMENT(0)]]
        in a tomb? He is not here, for he has risen! "
      comments:
      - number: 24:5
        content: "  The Aramaic text is literally \u201Cthe Life.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Have you forgotten what he said to you while he was still in Galilee: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018The destiny of the Son of Man is to be handed over to sinful
        men, to be nailed to a cross, and on the third day to rise again\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All at once they remembered his words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Leaving the tomb, they went to break the news to the Eleven and to
        all the others of what they had seen and heard. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:9
        content: '  For the sake of the English narrative, the information of v.   
          is included in v.  .    '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the disciples heard the testimony of the women, it made no sense,
        and they were unable to believe what they heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Jesus Walks to Emmaus'
      title: Jesus Walks to Emmaus
      number: 12
      content: But Peter jumped up and ran the entire distance to the tomb to see
        for himself. Stooping down, he looked inside and discovered it was empty!
        There was only the linen sheet lying there. Staggered by this, he walked
        away, wondering what it meant.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Later that same day, two of Jesus\u2019 disciples were walking from
        Jerusalem to Emmaus, [[COMMENT(0)]] a journey of about seventeen miles. "
      comments:
      - number: 24:13
        content: "  The Greek text states that the distance from Jerusalem to Emmaus
          was sixty stadia = seven miles in the majority of manuscripts. However
          some patristic writers such as Eusebius, Sozomen, and Jerome, as well as
          a few Greek manuscripts read one hundred sixty stadia which would be seventeen
          miles. There is an ancient site in modern-day Israel identified as Hamat
          (Emmaus) that is seventeen miles from Jerusalem and is known for its hot
          (burning) springs. The word    is taken from a Hebrew root that means \u201Cthe
          burning place.\u201D    "
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: 'They were in the midst of a discussion about all the events of the
        last few days when Jesus walked up and accompanied them in their journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: 'They were in the midst of a discussion about all the events of the
        last few days when Jesus walked up and accompanied them in their journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They were unaware that it was actually Jesus walking alongside them,
        for God prevented them from recognizing him.
      comments: []
    - name: '17-18: '
      title: 
      number: 17-18
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou seem to be in a deep discussion
        about something. What are you talking about, so sad and gloomy?\u201D</JESUS>They
        stopped, and the one named Cleopas [[COMMENT(0)]] answered, \u201CHaven\u2019t
        you heard? Are you the only one in Jerusalem unaware of the things that have
        happened over the last few days?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "24:17\u201318"
        content: "  Cleopas means \u201Cfrom a renowned father.\u201D Some scholars
          believe this could be the Clopas mentioned in  .    "
    - name: '17-18: '
      title: 
      number: 17-18
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou seem to be in a deep discussion
        about something. What are you talking about, so sad and gloomy?\u201D</JESUS>They
        stopped, and the one named Cleopas [[COMMENT(0)]] answered, \u201CHaven\u2019t
        you heard? Are you the only one in Jerusalem unaware of the things that have
        happened over the last few days?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "24:17\u201318"
        content: "  Cleopas means \u201Cfrom a renowned father.\u201D Some scholars
          believe this could be the Clopas mentioned in  .    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus asked, <JESUS>\u201CWhat things?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CThe things
        about Jesus, the man from Nazareth,\u201D they replied. \u201CHe was a mighty
        prophet of God who performed miracles and wonders. His words were powerful
        and he had great favor with God and the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: 'But three days ago the high priest and the rulers of the people sentenced
        him to death and had him crucified. We had all hoped that he was the one
        who would redeem and rescue Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20-21: '
      title: 
      number: 20-21
      content: 'But three days ago the high priest and the rulers of the people sentenced
        him to death and had him crucified. We had all hoped that he was the one
        who would redeem and rescue Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Early this morning, some of the women informed us of something amazing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They said they went to the tomb and found it empty. They claimed
        two angels appeared and told them that Jesus is now alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Some of us went to see for ourselves and found the tomb exactly as
        the women had said. But no one has seen him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhy are you so thick-headed? Why
        do you find it so hard to believe every word the prophets have spoken?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>Wasn\u2019t it necessary for the Messiah to experience all
        these sufferings and afterward to enter into his glory?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: And beginning with Moses and all the prophets he carefully unveiled
        to them the revelation of himself throughout the Scriptures.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'As they approached the village, Jesus walked on ahead, telling them
        he was going on to a distant place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "They urged him to remain there with them and pleaded, \u201CStay
        with us. It will be dark soon.\u201D So Jesus went with them into the village."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Joining them at the table for supper, he took bread and blessed it
        and broke it, then gave it to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: All at once their eyes were opened and they realized he was Jesus!
        Then suddenly, in a flash, Jesus vanished from before their eyes!
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Stunned, they looked at each other and said, \u201CWhy didn\u2019t
        we recognize him? Didn\u2019t our hearts burn with the flames of holy passion
        [[COMMENT(0)]] while we walked beside him? He unveiled for us such profound
        revelation from the Scriptures!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 24:32
        content: "  As translated from the Greek text. The Aramaic manuscript reads,
          \u201CWere not our hearts dull as he taught us?\u201D This is also the
          translation of the Latin text. The Aramaic words for \u201Cburning\u201D
          and \u201Cdull\u201D are almost identical.    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They left at once and hurried back to Jerusalem to tell the other
        disciples. When they found the Eleven and the other disciples all together, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "they overheard them saying, \u201CIt\u2019s really true! The Lord
        has risen from the dead. He even appeared to Peter!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Jesus Appears to the Disciples'
      title: Jesus Appears to the Disciples
      number: 35
      content: Then the two disciples told the others what had happened to them on
        the road to Emmaus and how Jesus had unveiled himself in the breaking of
        bread. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:35
        content: "  Luke\u2019s Gospel begins and ends with similar stories. In the
          beginning of Jesus\u2019 life we have the story of his parents walking
          off from Jerusalem and leaving him in the temple (), unaware that they
          had left Jesus behind. Luke ends with the story of Jesus walking alongside
          two disciples and they weren\u2019t aware of who was walking next to them.
          Both accounts were after the Feast. In both stories they were leaving Jerusalem.
          And both the Jewish scholars in the temple () and the two Emmaus road disciples
          () were astounded at what Jesus taught them.    "
    - name: '36-37: '
      title: 
      number: 36-37
      content: "While they were still discussing all of this, Jesus suddenly appeared
        right in front of their eyes! Startled and terrified, the disciples were
        convinced they were seeing a ghost. Standing there among them he said, <JESUS>\u201CBe
        at peace. I am the living God. Don\u2019t be afraid.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: "24:36\u201337"
        content: "  The words \u201CI am the living God. Don\u2019t be afraid\u201D
          are only found in the Aramaic text and the Latin Vulgate. The Greek text
          omits this sentence.    "
    - name: '36-37: '
      title: 
      number: 36-37
      content: "While they were still discussing all of this, Jesus suddenly appeared
        right in front of their eyes! Startled and terrified, the disciples were
        convinced they were seeing a ghost. Standing there among them he said, <JESUS>\u201CBe
        at peace. I am the living God. Don\u2019t be afraid.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: "24:36\u201337"
        content: "  The words \u201CI am the living God. Don\u2019t be afraid\u201D
          are only found in the Aramaic text and the Latin Vulgate. The Greek text
          omits this sentence.    "
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>Why are you so frightened? Don\u2019t let doubt enter your
        hearts.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>See my pierced hands and feet. See for yourselves, it is I,
        standing here alive. Touch me and know that my wounds are real. A spirit
        does not have a body of flesh and bone as you see that I have.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: Then he showed them his pierced hands and feet and let them touch
        his wounds. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:40
        content: '  Verse    is missing in some manuscripts.    '
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "The disciples were ecstatic, yet dumbfounded, unable to fully comprehend
        it.Knowing that they were still wondering if he was real, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CHere,
        let me show you. Give me something to eat.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '42-43: '
      title: 
      number: 42-43
      content: They handed him a piece of broiled fish and some honeycomb. And they
        watched him eat.
      comments: []
    - name: '42-43: '
      title: 
      number: 42-43
      content: They handed him a piece of broiled fish and some honeycomb. And they
        watched him eat.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Then he said to them, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t you remember the words
        that I spoke to you when I was still with you? I told you that I would fulfill
        everything written about me, including all the prophecies from the law of
        Moses through the Psalms and the writings of the prophets.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 24:44
        content: "  The Law, the prophets, and the \u201Cwritings\u201D make up the
          whole Old Testament (or  : an acronym of the first Hebrew letter from   
          [the five books of Moses],    [the prophets and historical books], and   
          [the writings]).    "
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'He supernaturally unlocked their understanding to receive the revelation
        of the Scriptures, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "and said to them, <JESUS>\u201CEverything that has happened fulfills
        what the Scriptures prophesied of me. The Messiah was destined to suffer
        and rise from the dead on the third day.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 24:46
        content: '  There is not an explicit reference to the Messiah dying and rising
          on the third day. This must have been on the symbolic level of interpreting
          Scripture. May Jesus open our understanding to the Bible to see it on this
          level.    '
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<JESUS>Now you must go into all the nations and preach repentance</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and forgiveness of sins so that they will turn to
        me. Start right here in Jerusalem,</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 24:47
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201Cgrace\u201D or \u201Cconversion.\u201D    "
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>for you are my witnesses and have seen for yourselves all
        that has transpired.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: The Ascension of Jesus'
      title: The Ascension of Jesus
      number: 49
      content: "<JESUS>I will send the fulfillment of the Father\u2019s promise</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to you, so stay here in the city until you are clothed
        with the</JESUS>  <JESUS>mighty</JESUS>  <JESUS>power of heaven.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 24:49
        content: "  The Aramaic reads \u201Cthe kingdom\u201D or \u201Crule.\u201D
          The Father\u2019s promise would be the coming of the Holy Spirit to live
          in them and empower them. See  .    "
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Jesus led his disciples out to Bethany. He lifted his hands over
        them and blessed them in his love. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'While he was still speaking words of love and blessing, he floated
        off the ground into the sky, ascending into heaven before their very eyes! '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And all they could do was worship him.Overwhelmed and ecstatic with
        joy, they made their way back to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: Every day they went to the temple, to praise and worship God. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 24:53
        content: '  So ends the glorious Gospel of Luke. The one who walked with
          his friends on the way to Emmaus wants to walk with us. May we never walk
          in sadness or unbelief, for Jesus has risen from the grave and lives victorious
          as the living God in resurrection life! May you pause here and rejoice,
          believing that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of the living God and the only
          one who will bring us to the Father. Trust in him alone to save you, and
          you will spend eternity with him.  '
